413namespace triton {
414 namespace arch {
415 namespace x86 {
416
417 x86Semantics::x86Semantics(triton::arch::Architecture* architecture,
418 triton::engines::symbolic::SymbolicEngine* symbolicEngine,
419 triton::engines::taint::TaintEngine* taintEngine,
420 const triton::modes::SharedModes& modes,
421 const triton::ast::SharedAstContext& astCtxt) : modes(modes), astCtxt(astCtxt) {
422
423 this->architecture = architecture;
424 this->exception = triton::arch::NO_FAULT;
425 this->symbolicEngine = symbolicEngine;
426 this->taintEngine = taintEngine;
427
428 if (architecture == nullptr)
429 throw triton::exceptions::Semantics("x86Semantics::x86Semantics(): The architecture API must be defined.");
430
431 if (this->symbolicEngine == nullptr)
432 throw triton::exceptions::Semantics("x86Semantics::x86Semantics(): The symbolic engine API must be defined.");
433
434 if (this->taintEngine == nullptr)
435 throw triton::exceptions::Semantics("x86Semantics::x86Semantics(): The taint engines API must be defined.");
436 }
437
438
439 triton::arch::exception_e x86Semantics::buildSemantics(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
440 switch (inst.getType()) {
441 case ID_INS_AAA: this->aaa_s(inst); break;

763 case ID_INS_VPADDD: this->vpaddd_s(inst); break;
764 case ID_INS_VPADDW: this->vpaddw_s(inst); break;
765 case ID_INS_VPAND: this->vpand_s(inst); break;
766 case ID_INS_VPANDN: this->vpandn_s(inst); break;
767 case ID_INS_VPERM2I128: this->vperm2i128_s(inst); break;
768 case ID_INS_VPERMQ: this->vpermq_s(inst); break;
769 case ID_INS_VPEXTRB: this->vpextrb_s(inst); break;
770 case ID_INS_VPEXTRD: this->vpextrd_s(inst); break;
771 case ID_INS_VPEXTRQ: this->vpextrq_s(inst); break;
772 case ID_INS_VPEXTRW: this->vpextrw_s(inst); break;
773 case ID_INS_VPBROADCASTB: this->vpbroadcastb_s(inst); break;
774 case ID_INS_VPCMPEQB: this->vpcmpeqb_s(inst); break;
775 case ID_INS_VPCMPEQD: this->vpcmpeqd_s(inst); break;
776 case ID_INS_VPCMPEQQ: this->vpcmpeqq_s(inst); break;
777 case ID_INS_VPCMPEQW: this->vpcmpeqw_s(inst); break;
778 case ID_INS_VPCMPGTB: this->vpcmpgtb_s(inst); break;
779 case ID_INS_VPCMPGTD: this->vpcmpgtd_s(inst); break;
780 case ID_INS_VPCMPGTW: this->vpcmpgtw_s(inst); break;
781 case ID_INS_VPMADDWD: this->vpmaddwd_s(inst); break;
782 case ID_INS_VPMOVMSKB: this->vpmovmskb_s(inst); break;
783 case ID_INS_VPMINUB: this->vpminub_s(inst); break;
784 case ID_INS_VPMULHW: this->vpmulhw_s(inst); break;
785 case ID_INS_VPMULLW: this->vpmullw_s(inst); break;
786 case ID_INS_VPOR: this->vpor_s(inst); break;
787 case ID_INS_VPSHUFD: this->vpshufd_s(inst); break;
788 case ID_INS_VPSIGNW: this->vpsignw_s(inst); break;
789 case ID_INS_VPSLLDQ: this->vpslldq_s(inst); break;
790 case ID_INS_VPSLLW: this->vpsllw_s(inst); break;
791 case ID_INS_VPSRAD: this->vpsrad_s(inst); break;
792 case ID_INS_VPSRAW: this->vpsraw_s(inst); break;
793 case ID_INS_VPSRLDQ: this->vpsrldq_s(inst); break;
794 case ID_INS_VPSRLW: this->vpsrlw_s(inst); break;
795 case ID_INS_VPSUBB: this->vpsubb_s(inst); break;
796 case ID_INS_VPSUBD: this->vpsubd_s(inst); break;
797 case ID_INS_VPSUBQ: this->vpsubq_s(inst); break;
798 case ID_INS_VPSUBW: this->vpsubw_s(inst); break;
799 case ID_INS_VPTEST: this->vptest_s(inst); break;
800 case ID_INS_VPUNPCKHBW: this->vpunpckhbw_s(inst); break;
801 case ID_INS_VPUNPCKHDQ: this->vpunpckhdq_s(inst); break;
802 case ID_INS_VPUNPCKHQDQ: this->vpunpckhqdq_s(inst); break;
803 case ID_INS_VPUNPCKHWD: this->vpunpckhwd_s(inst); break;
804 case ID_INS_VPUNPCKLBW: this->vpunpcklbw_s(inst); break;
805 case ID_INS_VPUNPCKLDQ: this->vpunpckldq_s(inst); break;
806 case ID_INS_VPUNPCKLQDQ: this->vpunpcklqdq_s(inst); break;
807 case ID_INS_VPUNPCKLWD: this->vpunpcklwd_s(inst); break;
808 case ID_INS_VPXOR: this->vpxor_s(inst); break;
809 case ID_INS_VXORPS: this->vxorps_s(inst); break;
810 case ID_INS_WAIT: this->wait_s(inst); break;
811 case ID_INS_WBINVD: this->wbinvd_s(inst); break;
812 case ID_INS_XADD: this->xadd_s(inst); break;
813 case ID_INS_XCHG: this->xchg_s(inst); break;
814 case ID_INS_XOR: this->xor_s(inst); break;
815 case ID_INS_XORPD: this->xorpd_s(inst); break;
816 case ID_INS_XORPS: this->xorps_s(inst); break;
817 default:
818 return triton::arch::FAULT_UD;
819 }
820 return this->exception;
821 }
822
823
824 triton::uint64 x86Semantics::alignAddStack_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst, triton::uint32 delta) {
825 auto dst = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getStackPointer());
826
827 /* Create symbolic operands */
828 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, dst);
829 auto op2 = this->astCtxt->bv(delta, dst.getBitSize());
830
831 /* Create the semantics */
832 auto node = this->astCtxt->bvadd(op1, op2);
833
834 /* Create symbolic expression */
835 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, dst, "Stack alignment");
836
837 /* Spread taint */
838 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, dst);
839
840 /* Return the new stack value */
841 return static_cast<triton::uint64>(node->evaluate());
842 }
843
844
845 triton::uint64 x86Semantics::alignSubStack_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst, triton::uint32 delta) {
846 auto dst = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getStackPointer());
847
848 /* Create symbolic operands */
849 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, dst);
850 auto op2 = this->astCtxt->bv(delta, dst.getBitSize());
851
852 /* Create the semantics */
853 auto node = this->astCtxt->bvsub(op1, op2);
854
855 /* Create symbolic expression */
856 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, dst, "Stack alignment");
857
858 /* Spread taint */
859 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, dst);
860
861 /* Return the new stack value */
862 return static_cast<triton::uint64>(node->evaluate());
863 }

865
866 void x86Semantics::clearFlag_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst, const triton::arch::Register& flag, std::string comment) {
867 /* Create the semantics */
868 auto node = this->astCtxt->bv(0, 1);
869
870 /* Create symbolic expression */
871 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, flag, comment);
872
873 /* Spread taint */
874 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->setTaintRegister(flag, triton::engines::taint::UNTAINTED);
875 }
876
877
878 void x86Semantics::setFlag_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst, const triton::arch::Register& flag, std::string comment) {
879 /* Create the semantics */
880 auto node = this->astCtxt->bv(1, 1);
881
882 /* Create symbolic expression */
883 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, flag, comment);
884
885 /* Spread taint */
886 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->setTaintRegister(flag, triton::engines::taint::UNTAINTED);
887 }
888
889
890 void x86Semantics::undefined_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst, const triton::arch::Register& reg) {
891 if (this->modes->isModeEnabled(triton::modes::CONCRETIZE_UNDEFINED_REGISTERS)) {
892 this->symbolicEngine->concretizeRegister(reg);
893 }
894 /* Tell that the instruction defines a register as undefined and untaint */
895 inst.setUndefinedRegister(reg);
896 this->taintEngine->setTaintRegister(reg, triton::engines::taint::UNTAINTED);
897 }
898
899
900 void x86Semantics::controlFlow_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
901 auto pc = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getProgramCounter());
902 auto counter = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getParentRegister(ID_REG_X86_CX));
903 auto zf = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_ZF));
904
905 switch (inst.getPrefix()) {
906
907 case triton::arch::x86::ID_PREFIX_REP: {
908 /* Create symbolic operands */
909 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, counter);
910
911 /* Create the semantics for Counter */
912 auto node1 = this->astCtxt->ite(
913 this->astCtxt->equal(op1, this->astCtxt->bv(0, counter.getBitSize())),
914 op1,
915 this->astCtxt->bvsub(op1, this->astCtxt->bv(1, counter.getBitSize()))
916 );
917
918 /* Create the semantics for PC */
919 auto node2 = this->astCtxt->ite(
920 this->astCtxt->equal(node1, this->astCtxt->bv(0, counter.getBitSize())),
921 this->astCtxt->bv(inst.getNextAddress(), pc.getBitSize()),
922 this->astCtxt->bv(inst.getAddress(), pc.getBitSize())
923 );
924
925 /* Create symbolic expression */
926 auto expr1 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node1, counter, "Counter operation");
927 auto expr2 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node2, pc, "Program Counter");
928
929 /* Spread taint for PC */
930 expr1->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(counter, counter);
931 expr2->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintAssignment(pc, counter);
932 break;
933 }
934
935 case triton::arch::x86::ID_PREFIX_REPE: {
936 /* Create symbolic operands */
937 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, counter);
938 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, zf);
939
940 /* Create the semantics for Counter */
941 auto node1 = this->astCtxt->ite(
942 this->astCtxt->equal(op1, this->astCtxt->bv(0, counter.getBitSize())),
943 op1,
944 this->astCtxt->bvsub(op1, this->astCtxt->bv(1, counter.getBitSize()))
945 );
946
947 /* Create the semantics for PC */
948 auto node2 = this->astCtxt->ite(
949 this->astCtxt->lor(
950 this->astCtxt->equal(node1, this->astCtxt->bv(0, counter.getBitSize())),
951 this->astCtxt->equal(op2, this->astCtxt->bvfalse())
952 ),
953 this->astCtxt->bv(inst.getNextAddress(), pc.getBitSize()),
954 this->astCtxt->bv(inst.getAddress(), pc.getBitSize())
955 );
956
957 /* Create symbolic expression */
958 auto expr1 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node1, counter, "Counter operation");
959 auto expr2 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node2, pc, "Program Counter");
960
961 /* Spread taint */
962 expr1->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(counter, counter);
963 expr2->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintAssignment(pc, counter);
964 break;
965 }
966
967 case triton::arch::x86::ID_PREFIX_REPNE: {
968 /* Create symbolic operands */
969 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, counter);
970 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, zf);
971
972 /* Create the semantics for Counter */
973 auto node1 = this->astCtxt->ite(
974 this->astCtxt->equal(op1, this->astCtxt->bv(0, counter.getBitSize())),
975 op1,
976 this->astCtxt->bvsub(op1, this->astCtxt->bv(1, counter.getBitSize()))
977 );
978
979 /* Create the semantics for PC */
980 auto node2 = this->astCtxt->ite(
981 this->astCtxt->lor(
982 this->astCtxt->equal(node1, this->astCtxt->bv(0, counter.getBitSize())),
983 this->astCtxt->equal(op2, this->astCtxt->bvtrue())
984 ),
985 this->astCtxt->bv(inst.getNextAddress(), pc.getBitSize()),
986 this->astCtxt->bv(inst.getAddress(), pc.getBitSize())
987 );
988
989 /* Create symbolic expression */
990 auto expr1 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node1, counter, "Counter operation");
991 auto expr2 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node2, pc, "Program Counter");
992
993 /* Spread taint */
994 expr1->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(counter, counter);
995 expr2->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintAssignment(pc, counter);
996 break;
997 }
998
999 default: {
1000 /* Create the semantics */
1001 auto node = this->astCtxt->bv(inst.getNextAddress(), pc.getBitSize());
1002
1003 /* Create symbolic expression */
1004 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicRegisterExpression(inst, node, this->architecture->getProgramCounter(), "Program Counter");
1005
1006 /* Spread taint */
1007 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->setTaintRegister(this->architecture->getProgramCounter(), triton::engines::taint::UNTAINTED);
1008 break;
1009 }
1010 }
1011 }
1012
1013
1015 void x86Semantics::updateFTW(triton::arch::Instruction& inst, const triton::engines::symbolic::SharedSymbolicExpression& parent) {
1016 /* Fetch the STX registers */
1017 auto st0 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_ST0));
1018 auto st1 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_ST1));
1019 auto st2 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_ST2));
1020 auto st3 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_ST3));
1021 auto st4 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_ST4));
1022 auto st5 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_ST5));
1023 auto st6 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_ST6));
1024 auto st7 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_ST7));
1025
1026 /* Fetch the STX ASTs */
1027 auto st0_ast = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, st0);
1028 auto st1_ast = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, st1);
1029 auto st2_ast = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, st2);
1030 auto st3_ast = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, st3);
1031 auto st4_ast = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, st4);
1032 auto st5_ast = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, st5);
1033 auto st6_ast = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, st6);
1034 auto st7_ast = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, st7);
1035
1036 /* Extract the fraction from the STX registers */
1037 auto fraction_st0 = this->astCtxt->extract(62, 0, st0_ast);
1038 auto fraction_st1 = this->astCtxt->extract(62, 0, st1_ast);
1039 auto fraction_st2 = this->astCtxt->extract(62, 0, st2_ast);
1040 auto fraction_st3 = this->astCtxt->extract(62, 0, st3_ast);
1041 auto fraction_st4 = this->astCtxt->extract(62, 0, st4_ast);
1042 auto fraction_st5 = this->astCtxt->extract(62, 0, st5_ast);
1043 auto fraction_st6 = this->astCtxt->extract(62, 0, st6_ast);
1044 auto fraction_st7 = this->astCtxt->extract(62, 0, st7_ast);
1045
1046 /* Extract the integer bit from the STX registers */
1047 auto integer_st0 = this->astCtxt->extract(63, 63, st0_ast);
1048 auto integer_st1 = this->astCtxt->extract(63, 63, st1_ast);
1049 auto integer_st2 = this->astCtxt->extract(63, 63, st2_ast);
1050 auto integer_st3 = this->astCtxt->extract(63, 63, st3_ast);
1051 auto integer_st4 = this->astCtxt->extract(63, 63, st4_ast);
1052 auto integer_st5 = this->astCtxt->extract(63, 63, st5_ast);
1053 auto integer_st6 = this->astCtxt->extract(63, 63, st6_ast);
1054 auto integer_st7 = this->astCtxt->extract(63, 63, st7_ast);
1055
1056 /* Extract the exponent from the STX registers */
1057 auto exponent_st0 = this->astCtxt->extract(79, 64, st0_ast);
1058 auto exponent_st1 = this->astCtxt->extract(79, 64, st1_ast);
1059 auto exponent_st2 = this->astCtxt->extract(79, 64, st2_ast);
1060 auto exponent_st3 = this->astCtxt->extract(79, 64, st3_ast);
1061 auto exponent_st4 = this->astCtxt->extract(79, 64, st4_ast);
1062 auto exponent_st5 = this->astCtxt->extract(79, 64, st5_ast);
1063 auto exponent_st6 = this->astCtxt->extract(79, 64, st6_ast);
1064 auto exponent_st7 = this->astCtxt->extract(79, 64, st7_ast);
1065
1066 /* Exponent All Zeros */
1067 auto ea0_st0 = this->astCtxt->equal(exponent_st0, this->astCtxt->bv(0x0000, 16));
1068 auto ea0_st1 = this->astCtxt->equal(exponent_st1, this->astCtxt->bv(0x0000, 16));
1069 auto ea0_st2 = this->astCtxt->equal(exponent_st2, this->astCtxt->bv(0x0000, 16));
1070 auto ea0_st3 = this->astCtxt->equal(exponent_st3, this->astCtxt->bv(0x0000, 16));
1071 auto ea0_st4 = this->astCtxt->equal(exponent_st4, this->astCtxt->bv(0x0000, 16));
1072 auto ea0_st5 = this->astCtxt->equal(exponent_st5, this->astCtxt->bv(0x0000, 16));
1073 auto ea0_st6 = this->astCtxt->equal(exponent_st6, this->astCtxt->bv(0x0000, 16));
1074 auto ea0_st7 = this->astCtxt->equal(exponent_st7, this->astCtxt->bv(0x0000, 16));
1075
1076 /* Exponent All Ones */
1077 auto ea1_st0 = this->astCtxt->equal(exponent_st0, this->astCtxt->bv(0xFFFF, 16));
1078 auto ea1_st1 = this->astCtxt->equal(exponent_st1, this->astCtxt->bv(0xFFFF, 16));
1079 auto ea1_st2 = this->astCtxt->equal(exponent_st2, this->astCtxt->bv(0xFFFF, 16));
1080 auto ea1_st3 = this->astCtxt->equal(exponent_st3, this->astCtxt->bv(0xFFFF, 16));
1081 auto ea1_st4 = this->astCtxt->equal(exponent_st4, this->astCtxt->bv(0xFFFF, 16));
1082 auto ea1_st5 = this->astCtxt->equal(exponent_st5, this->astCtxt->bv(0xFFFF, 16));
1083 auto ea1_st6 = this->astCtxt->equal(exponent_st6, this->astCtxt->bv(0xFFFF, 16));
1084 auto ea1_st7 = this->astCtxt->equal(exponent_st7, this->astCtxt->bv(0xFFFF, 16));
1085
1086 /* Exponent Neither All Zeroes Or Ones */
1087 auto ena01_st0 = this->astCtxt->equal(this->astCtxt->lor(ea0_st0, ea1_st0), this->astCtxt->bvfalse());
1088 auto ena01_st1 = this->astCtxt->equal(this->astCtxt->lor(ea0_st1, ea1_st1), this->astCtxt->bvfalse());
1089 auto ena01_st2 = this->astCtxt->equal(this->astCtxt->lor(ea0_st2, ea1_st2), this->astCtxt->bvfalse());
1090 auto ena01_st3 = this->astCtxt->equal(this->astCtxt->lor(ea0_st3, ea1_st3), this->astCtxt->bvfalse());
1091 auto ena01_st4 = this->astCtxt->equal(this->astCtxt->lor(ea0_st4, ea1_st4), this->astCtxt->bvfalse());
1092 auto ena01_st5 = this->astCtxt->equal(this->astCtxt->lor(ea0_st5, ea1_st5), this->astCtxt->bvfalse());
1093 auto ena01_st6 = this->astCtxt->equal(this->astCtxt->lor(ea0_st6, ea1_st6), this->astCtxt->bvfalse());
1094 auto ena01_st7 = this->astCtxt->equal(this->astCtxt->lor(ea0_st7, ea1_st7), this->astCtxt->bvfalse());
1095
1096 /* Integer Bit 0 */
1097 auto ib0_st0 = this->astCtxt->equal(integer_st0, this->astCtxt->bv(0, 1));
1098 auto ib0_st1 = this->astCtxt->equal(integer_st1, this->astCtxt->bv(0, 1));
1099 auto ib0_st2 = this->astCtxt->equal(integer_st2, this->astCtxt->bv(0, 1));
1100 auto ib0_st3 = this->astCtxt->equal(integer_st3, this->astCtxt->bv(0, 1));
1101 auto ib0_st4 = this->astCtxt->equal(integer_st4, this->astCtxt->bv(0, 1));
1102 auto ib0_st5 = this->astCtxt->equal(integer_st5, this->astCtxt->bv(0, 1));
1103 auto ib0_st6 = this->astCtxt->equal(integer_st6, this->astCtxt->bv(0, 1));
1104 auto ib0_st7 = this->astCtxt->equal(integer_st7, this->astCtxt->bv(0, 1));
1105
1106 /* Fraction All Zeroes */
1107 auto fa0_st0 = this->astCtxt->equal(fraction_st0, this->astCtxt->bv(0, 63));
1108 auto fa0_st1 = this->astCtxt->equal(fraction_st1, this->astCtxt->bv(0, 63));
1109 auto fa0_st2 = this->astCtxt->equal(fraction_st2, this->astCtxt->bv(0, 63));
1110 auto fa0_st3 = this->astCtxt->equal(fraction_st3, this->astCtxt->bv(0, 63));
1111 auto fa0_st4 = this->astCtxt->equal(fraction_st4, this->astCtxt->bv(0, 63));
1112 auto fa0_st5 = this->astCtxt->equal(fraction_st5, this->astCtxt->bv(0, 63));
1113 auto fa0_st6 = this->astCtxt->equal(fraction_st6, this->astCtxt->bv(0, 63));
1114 auto fa0_st7 = this->astCtxt->equal(fraction_st7, this->astCtxt->bv(0, 63));
1115
1116 /* Determine the x87 FPU Tag Word (Diagram at page 379 of the AMD Architecture Programmer's Manual, Volume 2: System Programming) */
1117 auto db_1_0 = this->astCtxt->ite(ea0_st0,
1118 this->astCtxt->ite(ib0_st0,
1119 this->astCtxt->ite(fa0_st0,
1120 this->astCtxt->bv(1, 2), // 'Exponent All 0' + 'Integer Bit 0' + 'Fraction All 0'
1121 this->astCtxt->bv(2, 2)), // 'Exponent All 0' + 'Integer Bit 0' + 'Fraction Not All 0'
1122 this->astCtxt->bv(2, 2)), // 'Exponent All 0' + 'Integer Bit 1'
1123 this->astCtxt->ite(ena01_st0,
1124 this->astCtxt->ite(ib0_st0,
1125 this->astCtxt->bv(2, 2), // 'Exponent Not All 0/1' + 'Integer Bit 0'
1126 this->astCtxt->bv(0, 2)), // 'Exponent Not All 0/1' + 'Integer Bit 1'
1127 this->astCtxt->bv(2, 2))); // 'Exponent All 1'
1128
1129 auto db_3_2 = this->astCtxt->ite(ea0_st1,
1130 this->astCtxt->ite(ib0_st1,
1131 this->astCtxt->ite(fa0_st1,
1132 this->astCtxt->bv(1, 2), // 'Exponent All 0' + 'Integer Bit 0' + 'Fraction All 0'
1133 this->astCtxt->bv(2, 2)), // 'Exponent All 0' + 'Integer Bit 0' + 'Fraction Not All 0'
1134 this->astCtxt->bv(2, 2)), // 'Exponent All 0' + 'Integer Bit 1'
1135 this->astCtxt->ite(ena01_st1,
1136 this->astCtxt->ite(ib0_st1,
1137 this->astCtxt->bv(2, 2), // 'Exponent Not All 0/1' + 'Integer Bit 0'
1138 this->astCtxt->bv(0, 2)), // 'Exponent Not All 0/1' + 'Integer Bit 1'
1139 this->astCtxt->bv(2, 2))); // 'Exponent All 1'
1140
1141 auto db_5_4 = this->astCtxt->ite(ea0_st2,
1142 this->astCtxt->ite(ib0_st2,
1143 this->astCtxt->ite(fa0_st2,
1144 this->astCtxt->bv(1, 2), // 'Exponent All 0' + 'Integer Bit 0' + 'Fraction All 0'
1145 this->astCtxt->bv(2, 2)), // 'Exponent All 0' + 'Integer Bit 0' + 'Fraction Not All 0'
1146 this->astCtxt->bv(2, 2)), // 'Exponent All 0' + 'Integer Bit 1'
1147 this->astCtxt->ite(ena01_st2,
1148 this->astCtxt->ite(ib0_st2,
1149 this->astCtxt->bv(2, 2), // 'Exponent Not All 0/1' + 'Integer Bit 0'
1150 this->astCtxt->bv(0, 2)), // 'Exponent Not All 0/1' + 'Integer Bit 1'
1151 this->astCtxt->bv(2, 2))); // 'Exponent All 1'
1152
1153 auto db_7_6 = this->astCtxt->ite(ea0_st3,
1154 this->astCtxt->ite(ib0_st3,
1155 this->astCtxt->ite(fa0_st3,
1156 this->astCtxt->bv(1, 2), // 'Exponent All 0' + 'Integer Bit 0' + 'Fraction All 0'
1157 this->astCtxt->bv(2, 2)), // 'Exponent All 0' + 'Integer Bit 0' + 'Fraction Not All 0'
1158 this->astCtxt->bv(2, 2)), // 'Exponent All 0' + 'Integer Bit 1'
1159 this->astCtxt->ite(ena01_st3,
1160 this->astCtxt->ite(ib0_st3,
1161 this->astCtxt->bv(2, 2), // 'Exponent Not All 0/1' + 'Integer Bit 0'
1162 this->astCtxt->bv(0, 2)), // 'Exponent Not All 0/1' + 'Integer Bit 1'
1163 this->astCtxt->bv(2, 2))); // 'Exponent All 1'
1164
1165 auto db_9_8 = this->astCtxt->ite(ea0_st4,
1166 this->astCtxt->ite(ib0_st4,
1167 this->astCtxt->ite(fa0_st4,
1168 this->astCtxt->bv(1, 2), // 'Exponent All 0' + 'Integer Bit 0' + 'Fraction All 0'
1169 this->astCtxt->bv(2, 2)), // 'Exponent All 0' + 'Integer Bit 0' + 'Fraction Not All 0'
1170 this->astCtxt->bv(2, 2)), // 'Exponent All 0' + 'Integer Bit 1'
1171 this->astCtxt->ite(ena01_st4,
1172 this->astCtxt->ite(ib0_st4,
1173 this->astCtxt->bv(2, 2), // 'Exponent Not All 0/1' + 'Integer Bit 0'
1174 this->astCtxt->bv(0, 2)), // 'Exponent Not All 0/1' + 'Integer Bit 1'
1175 this->astCtxt->bv(2, 2))); // 'Exponent All 1'
1176
1177 auto db_11_10 = this->astCtxt->ite(ea0_st5,
1178 this->astCtxt->ite(ib0_st5,
1179 this->astCtxt->ite(fa0_st5,
1180 this->astCtxt->bv(1, 2), // 'Exponent All 0' + 'Integer Bit 0' + 'Fraction All 0'
1181 this->astCtxt->bv(2, 2)), // 'Exponent All 0' + 'Integer Bit 0' + 'Fraction Not All 0'
1182 this->astCtxt->bv(2, 2)), // 'Exponent All 0' + 'Integer Bit 1'
1183 this->astCtxt->ite(ena01_st5,
1184 this->astCtxt->ite(ib0_st5,
1185 this->astCtxt->bv(2, 2), // 'Exponent Not All 0/1' + 'Integer Bit 0'
1186 this->astCtxt->bv(0, 2)), // 'Exponent Not All 0/1' + 'Integer Bit 1'
1187 this->astCtxt->bv(2, 2))); // 'Exponent All 1'
1188
1189 auto db_13_12 = this->astCtxt->ite(ea0_st6,
1190 this->astCtxt->ite(ib0_st6,
1191 this->astCtxt->ite(fa0_st6,
1192 this->astCtxt->bv(1, 2), // 'Exponent All 0' + 'Integer Bit 0' + 'Fraction All 0'
1193 this->astCtxt->bv(2, 2)), // 'Exponent All 0' + 'Integer Bit 0' + 'Fraction Not All 0'
1194 this->astCtxt->bv(2, 2)), // 'Exponent All 0' + 'Integer Bit 1'
1195 this->astCtxt->ite(ena01_st6,
1196 this->astCtxt->ite(ib0_st6,
1197 this->astCtxt->bv(2, 2), // 'Exponent Not All 0/1' + 'Integer Bit 0'
1198 this->astCtxt->bv(0, 2)), // 'Exponent Not All 0/1' + 'Integer Bit 1'
1199 this->astCtxt->bv(2, 2))); // 'Exponent All 1'
1200
1201 auto db_15_14 = this->astCtxt->ite(ea0_st7,
1202 this->astCtxt->ite(ib0_st7,
1203 this->astCtxt->ite(fa0_st7,
1204 this->astCtxt->bv(1, 2), // 'Exponent All 0' + 'Integer Bit 0' + 'Fraction All 0'
1205 this->astCtxt->bv(2, 2)), // 'Exponent All 0' + 'Integer Bit 0' + 'Fraction Not All 0'
1206 this->astCtxt->bv(2, 2)), // 'Exponent All 0' + 'Integer Bit 1'
1207 this->astCtxt->ite(ena01_st7,
1208 this->astCtxt->ite(ib0_st7,
1209 this->astCtxt->bv(2, 2), // 'Exponent Not All 0/1' + 'Integer Bit 0'
1210 this->astCtxt->bv(0, 2)), // 'Exponent Not All 0/1' + 'Integer Bit 1'
1211 this->astCtxt->bv(2, 2))); // 'Exponent All 1'
1212
1213 /* Restore the x87 FPU Tag Word */
1214 auto node = this->astCtxt->concat(db_15_14,
1215 this->astCtxt->concat(db_13_12,
1216 this->astCtxt->concat(db_11_10,
1217 this->astCtxt->concat(db_9_8,
1218 this->astCtxt->concat(db_7_6,
1219 this->astCtxt->concat(db_5_4,
1220 this->astCtxt->concat(db_3_2, db_1_0)))))));
1221
1222 /* Create the symbolic expression */
1223 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_FTW), "x87 FPU Tag Word");
1224
1225 /* Spread the taint from the parent to the child */
1226 auto st0_taint = this->taintEngine->isRegisterTainted(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_ST0));
1227 auto st1_taint = this->taintEngine->isRegisterTainted(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_ST1));
1228 auto st2_taint = this->taintEngine->isRegisterTainted(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_ST2));
1229 auto st3_taint = this->taintEngine->isRegisterTainted(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_ST3));
1230 auto st4_taint = this->taintEngine->isRegisterTainted(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_ST4));
1231 auto st5_taint = this->taintEngine->isRegisterTainted(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_ST5));
1232 auto st6_taint = this->taintEngine->isRegisterTainted(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_ST6));
1233 auto st7_taint = this->taintEngine->isRegisterTainted(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_ST7));
1234
1235 auto is_ftw_tainted = st0_taint | st1_taint | st2_taint | st3_taint |
1236 st4_taint | st5_taint | st6_taint | st7_taint;
1237
1238 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->setTaintRegister(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_FTW), is_ftw_tainted);
1239 }
1240
1241
1242 void x86Semantics::af_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst,
1243 const triton::engines::symbolic::SharedSymbolicExpression& parent,
1244 triton::arch::OperandWrapper& dst,
1245 const triton::ast::SharedAbstractNode& op1,
1246 const triton::ast::SharedAbstractNode& op2,
1247 bool vol) {
1248
1249 auto bvSize = dst.getBitSize();
1250 auto low = vol ? 0 : dst.getLow();
1251 auto high = vol ? bvSize-1 : dst.getHigh();
1252
1253 /*
1254 * Create the semantic.
1255 * af = 0x10 == (0x10 & (regDst ^ op1 ^ op2))
1256 */
1257 auto node = this->astCtxt->ite(
1258 this->astCtxt->equal(
1259 this->astCtxt->bv(0x10, bvSize),
1260 this->astCtxt->bvand(
1261 this->astCtxt->bv(0x10, bvSize),
1262 this->astCtxt->bvxor(
1263 this->astCtxt->extract(high, low, this->astCtxt->reference(parent)),
1264 this->astCtxt->bvxor(op1, op2)
1265 )
1266 )
1267 ),
1268 this->astCtxt->bv(1, 1),
1269 this->astCtxt->bv(0, 1)
1270 );
1271
1272 /* Create the symbolic expression */
1273 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_AF), "Adjust flag");
1274
1275 /* Spread the taint from the parent to the child */
1276 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->setTaintRegister(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_AF), parent->isTainted);
1277 }

1280 void x86Semantics::afAaa_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst,
1281 const triton::engines::symbolic::SharedSymbolicExpression& parent,
1282 triton::arch::OperandWrapper& dst,
1283 const triton::ast::SharedAbstractNode& op1,
1284 const triton::ast::SharedAbstractNode& op3,
1285 bool vol) {
1286
1287 auto bvSize = dst.getBitSize();
1288
1289 /*
1290 * Create the semantic.
1291 * af = 1 if ((AL AND 0FH) > 9) or (AF = 1) then 0
1292 */
1293 auto node = this->astCtxt->ite(
1294 this->astCtxt->lor(
1295 this->astCtxt->bvugt(
1296 this->astCtxt->bvand(op1, this->astCtxt->bv(0xf, bvSize)),
1297 this->astCtxt->bv(9, bvSize)
1298 ),
1299 this->astCtxt->equal(op3, this->astCtxt->bvtrue())
1300 ),
1301 this->astCtxt->bv(1, 1),
1302 this->astCtxt->bv(0, 1)
1303 );
1304
1305 /* Create the symbolic expression */
1306 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_AF), "Adjust flag");
1307
1308 /* Spread the taint from the parent to the child */
1309 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->setTaintRegister(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_AF), parent->isTainted);
1310 }

1382
1383 void x86Semantics::cfAdd_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst,
1384 const triton::engines::symbolic::SharedSymbolicExpression& parent,
1385 triton::arch::OperandWrapper& dst,
1386 const triton::ast::SharedAbstractNode& op1,
1387 const triton::ast::SharedAbstractNode& op2,
1388 bool vol) {
1389
1390 auto bvSize = dst.getBitSize();
1391 auto low = vol ? 0 : dst.getLow();
1392 auto high = vol ? bvSize-1 : dst.getHigh();
1393
1394 /*
1395 * Create the semantic.
1396 * cf = MSB((op1 & op2) ^ ((op1 ^ op2 ^ parent) & (op1 ^ op2)));
1397 */
1398 auto node = this->astCtxt->extract(bvSize-1, bvSize-1,
1399 this->astCtxt->bvxor(
1400 this->astCtxt->bvand(op1, op2),
1401 this->astCtxt->bvand(
1402 this->astCtxt->bvxor(
1403 this->astCtxt->bvxor(op1, op2),
1404 this->astCtxt->extract(high, low, this->astCtxt->reference(parent))
1405 ),
1406 this->astCtxt->bvxor(op1, op2))
1407 )
1408 );
1409
1410 /* Create the symbolic expression */
1411 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_CF), "Carry flag");
1412
1413 /* Spread the taint from the parent to the child */
1414 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->setTaintRegister(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_CF), parent->isTainted);
1415 }

1641
1642 void x86Semantics::cfRcl_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst,
1643 const triton::engines::symbolic::SharedSymbolicExpression& parent,
1644 const triton::ast::SharedAbstractNode& result,
1645 const triton::ast::SharedAbstractNode& op2,
1646 bool vol) {
1647
1648 auto bvSize = op2->getBitvectorSize();
1649 auto high = result->getBitvectorSize() - 1;
1650 auto cf = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_CF));
1651
1652 auto node = this->astCtxt->ite(
1653 this->astCtxt->equal(op2, this->astCtxt->bv(0, bvSize)),
1654 this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(cf),
1655 this->astCtxt->extract(high, high, result)
1656 );
1657
1658 /* Create the symbolic expression */
1659 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, cf.getConstRegister(), "Carry flag");
1660
1661 if (op2->evaluate()) {
1662 /* Spread the taint from the parent to the child */
1663 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->setTaintRegister(cf.getConstRegister(), parent->isTainted);
1664 }
1665 else {
1666 inst.removeWrittenRegister(cf.getConstRegister());
1667 }
1668 }

1670
1671 void x86Semantics::cfRcr_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst,
1672 const triton::engines::symbolic::SharedSymbolicExpression& parent,
1673 triton::arch::OperandWrapper& dst,
1674 const triton::ast::SharedAbstractNode& result,
1675 const triton::ast::SharedAbstractNode& op2,
1676 bool vol) {
1677
1678 auto bvSize = op2->getBitvectorSize();
1679 auto high = result->getBitvectorSize() - 1;
1680 auto cf = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_CF));
1681
1682 auto node = this->astCtxt->ite(
1683 this->astCtxt->equal(op2, this->astCtxt->bv(0, bvSize)),
1684 this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(cf),
1685 this->astCtxt->extract(high, high, result) /* yes it's should be LSB, but here it's a trick :-) */
1686 );
1687
1688 /* Create the symbolic expression */
1689 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, cf.getConstRegister(), "Carry flag");
1690
1691 if (op2->evaluate()) {
1692 /* Spread the taint from the parent to the child */
1693 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->setTaintRegister(cf.getConstRegister(), parent->isTainted);
1694 }
1695 else {
1696 inst.removeWrittenRegister(cf.getConstRegister());
1697 }
1698 }

1758
1759 void x86Semantics::cfSar_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst,
1760 const triton::engines::symbolic::SharedSymbolicExpression& parent,
1761 triton::arch::OperandWrapper& dst,
1762 const triton::ast::SharedAbstractNode& op1,
1763 const triton::ast::SharedAbstractNode& op2,
1764 bool vol) {
1765
1766 auto bvSize = dst.getBitSize();
1767 auto cf = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_CF));
1768
1769 /*
1770 * Create the semantic.
1771 * if op2 != 0:
1772 * if op2 > bvSize:
1773 * cf.id = ((op1 >> (bvSize - 1)) & 1)
1774 * else:
1775 * cf.id = ((op1 >> (op2 - 1)) & 1)
1776 */
1777 auto node = this->astCtxt->ite(
1778 this->astCtxt->equal(op2, this->astCtxt->bv(0, bvSize)),
1779 this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(cf),
1780 this->astCtxt->ite(
1781 this->astCtxt->bvugt(op2, this->astCtxt->bv(bvSize, bvSize)),
1782 this->astCtxt->extract(0, 0, this->astCtxt->bvlshr(op1, this->astCtxt->bvsub(this->astCtxt->bv(bvSize, bvSize), this->astCtxt->bv(1, bvSize)))),
1783 this->astCtxt->extract(0, 0, this->astCtxt->bvlshr(op1, this->astCtxt->bvsub(op2, this->astCtxt->bv(1, bvSize))))
1784 )
1785 );
1786
1787 /* Create the symbolic expression */
1788 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, cf.getConstRegister(), "Carry flag");
1789
1790 if (op2->evaluate()) {
1791 /* Spread the taint from the parent to the child */
1792 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->setTaintRegister(cf.getConstRegister(), parent->isTainted);
1793 }
1794 else {
1795 inst.removeWrittenRegister(cf.getConstRegister());
1796 }
1797 }

1800 void x86Semantics::cfShl_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst,
1801 const triton::engines::symbolic::SharedSymbolicExpression& parent,
1802 triton::arch::OperandWrapper& dst,
1803 const triton::ast::SharedAbstractNode& op1,
1804 const triton::ast::SharedAbstractNode& op2,
1805 bool vol) {
1806
1807 auto bvSize = dst.getBitSize();
1808 auto cf = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_CF));
1809
1810 /*
1811 * Create the semantic.
1812 * cf = (op1 >> ((bvSize - op2) & 1) if op2 != 0
1813 */
1814 auto node = this->astCtxt->ite(
1815 this->astCtxt->equal(op2, this->astCtxt->bv(0, bvSize)),
1816 this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(cf),
1817 this->astCtxt->extract(0, 0,
1818 this->astCtxt->bvlshr(
1819 op1,
1820 this->astCtxt->bvsub(
1821 this->astCtxt->bv(bvSize, bvSize),
1822 op2
1823 )
1824 )
1825 )
1826 );
1827
1828 /* Create the symbolic expression */
1829 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, cf.getConstRegister(), "Carry flag");
1830
1831 if (op2->evaluate()) {
1832 /* Spread the taint from the parent to the child */
1833 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->setTaintRegister(cf.getConstRegister(), parent->isTainted);
1834 }
1835 else {
1836 inst.removeWrittenRegister(cf.getConstRegister());
1837 }
1838 }

1841 void x86Semantics::cfShld_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst,
1842 const triton::engines::symbolic::SharedSymbolicExpression& parent,
1843 triton::arch::OperandWrapper& dst,
1844 const triton::ast::SharedAbstractNode& op1,
1845 const triton::ast::SharedAbstractNode& op2,
1846 const triton::ast::SharedAbstractNode& op3,
1847 bool vol) {
1848
1849 auto bv1Size = op1->getBitvectorSize();
1850 auto bv2Size = op2->getBitvectorSize();
1851 auto bv3Size = op3->getBitvectorSize();
1852 auto cf = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_CF));
1853
1854 /*
1855 * Create the semantic.
1856 * cf = MSB(rol(op3, concat(op2,op1))) if op3 != 0
1857 */
1858 auto node = this->astCtxt->ite(
1859 this->astCtxt->equal(op3, this->astCtxt->bv(0, bv3Size)),
1860 this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(cf),
1861 this->astCtxt->extract(
1862 dst.getBitSize(), dst.getBitSize(),
1863 this->astCtxt->bvrol(
1864 this->astCtxt->concat(op2, op1),
1865 this->astCtxt->zx(((bv1Size + bv2Size) - bv3Size), op3)
1866 )
1867 )
1868 );
1869
1870 /* Create the symbolic expression */
1871 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, cf.getConstRegister(), "Carry flag");
1872
1873 if (op3->evaluate()) {
1874 /* Spread the taint from the parent to the child */
1875 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->setTaintRegister(cf.getConstRegister(), parent->isTainted);
1876 }
1877 else {
1878 inst.removeWrittenRegister(cf.getConstRegister());
1879 }
1880 }

1923 void x86Semantics::cfShrd_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst,
1924 const triton::engines::symbolic::SharedSymbolicExpression& parent,
1925 triton::arch::OperandWrapper& dst,
1926 const triton::ast::SharedAbstractNode& op1,
1927 const triton::ast::SharedAbstractNode& op2,
1928 const triton::ast::SharedAbstractNode& op3,
1929 bool vol) {
1930
1931 auto bvSize = dst.getBitSize();
1932 auto bv1Size = op1->getBitvectorSize();
1933 auto bv2Size = op2->getBitvectorSize();
1934 auto bv3Size = op3->getBitvectorSize();
1935 auto cf = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_CF));
1936
1937 /*
1938 * Create the semantic.
1939 * cf = MSB(ror(op3, concat(op2,op1))) if op3 != 0
1940 */
1941 auto node = this->astCtxt->ite(
1942 this->astCtxt->equal(op3, this->astCtxt->bv(0, bv3Size)),
1943 this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(cf),
1944 this->astCtxt->extract(
1945 (bvSize * 2) - 1, (bvSize * 2) - 1,
1946 this->astCtxt->bvror(
1947 this->astCtxt->concat(op2, op1),
1948 this->astCtxt->zx(((bv1Size + bv2Size) - bv3Size), op3)
1949 )
1950 )
1951 );
1952
1953 /* Create the symbolic expression */
1954 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, cf.getConstRegister(), "Carry flag");
1955
1956 if (op3->evaluate()) {
1957 /* Spread the taint from the parent to the child */
1958 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->setTaintRegister(cf.getConstRegister(), parent->isTainted);
1959 }
1960 else {
1961 inst.removeWrittenRegister(cf.getConstRegister());
1962 }
1963 }

1965
1966 void x86Semantics::cfSub_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst,
1967 const triton::engines::symbolic::SharedSymbolicExpression& parent,
1968 triton::arch::OperandWrapper& dst,
1969 const triton::ast::SharedAbstractNode& op1,
1970 const triton::ast::SharedAbstractNode& op2,
1971 bool vol) {
1972
1973 auto bvSize = dst.getBitSize();
1974 auto low = vol ? 0 : dst.getLow();
1975 auto high = vol ? bvSize-1 : dst.getHigh();
1976
1977 /*
1978 * Create the semantic.
1979 * cf = extract(bvSize, bvSize (((op1 ^ op2 ^ res) ^ ((op1 ^ res) & (op1 ^ op2)))))
1980 */
1981 auto node = this->astCtxt->extract(bvSize-1, bvSize-1,
1982 this->astCtxt->bvxor(
1983 this->astCtxt->bvxor(op1, this->astCtxt->bvxor(op2, this->astCtxt->extract(high, low, this->astCtxt->reference(parent)))),
1984 this->astCtxt->bvand(
1985 this->astCtxt->bvxor(op1, this->astCtxt->extract(high, low, this->astCtxt->reference(parent))),
1986 this->astCtxt->bvxor(op1, op2)
1987 )
1988 )
1989 );
1990
1991 /* Create the symbolic expression */
1992 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_CF), "Carry flag");
1993
1994 /* Spread the taint from the parent to the child */
1995 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->setTaintRegister(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_CF), parent->isTainted);
1996 }

2030 void x86Semantics::ofAdd_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst,
2031 const triton::engines::symbolic::SharedSymbolicExpression& parent,
2032 triton::arch::OperandWrapper& dst,
2033 const triton::ast::SharedAbstractNode& op1,

2038 auto low = vol ? 0 : dst.getLow();
2039 auto high = vol ? bvSize-1 : dst.getHigh();
2040
2041 /*
2042 * Create the semantic.
2043 * of = MSB((op1 ^ ~op2) & (op1 ^ regDst))
2044 */
2045 auto node = this->astCtxt->extract(bvSize-1, bvSize-1,
2046 this->astCtxt->bvand(
2047 this->astCtxt->bvxor(op1, this->astCtxt->bvnot(op2)),
2048 this->astCtxt->bvxor(op1, this->astCtxt->extract(high, low, this->astCtxt->reference(parent)))
2049 )
2050 );
2051
2052 /* Create the symbolic expression */
2053 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_OF), "Overflow flag");

2055 /* Spread the taint from the parent to the child */
2056 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->setTaintRegister(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_OF), parent->isTainted);

2249
2250 auto bvSize = dst.getBitSize();
2251 auto of = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_OF));
2252
2253 /*
2254 * Create the semantic.
2255 * of = 0 if op2 == 1
2256 */
2257 auto node = this->astCtxt->ite(
2258 this->astCtxt->land(
2259 this->astCtxt->equal(
2260 /* #672 */
2261 this->astCtxt->reference(parent),
2262 this->astCtxt->reference(parent)
2263 /* ---- */
2264 ),
2265 this->astCtxt->equal(
2266 op2,
2267 this->astCtxt->bv(1, bvSize)
2268 )
2269 ),
2270 this->astCtxt->bv(0, 1),
2271 this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(of)
2272 );
2273
2274 /* Create the symbolic expression */
2275 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, of.getConstRegister(), "Overflow flag");
2276
2277 if (op2->evaluate()) {
2278 /* Spread the taint from the parent to the child */
2279 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->setTaintRegister(of.getConstRegister(), parent->isTainted);
2280 }
2281 else {
2282 inst.removeWrittenRegister(of.getConstRegister());
2283 }
2284 }

2309 )
2310 ),

2312 );

2318 /* Spread the taint from the parent to the child */

2438 )

2441 ),
2442 this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(of)
2443 );

2458 void x86Semantics::ofSub_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst,
2459 const triton::engines::symbolic::SharedSymbolicExpression& parent,
2460 triton::arch::OperandWrapper& dst,
2461 const triton::ast::SharedAbstractNode& op1,
2462 const triton::ast::SharedAbstractNode& op2,
2463 bool vol) {
2464
2465 auto bvSize = dst.getBitSize();
2466 auto low = vol ? 0 : dst.getLow();
2467 auto high = vol ? bvSize-1 : dst.getHigh();
2468
2469 /*
2470 * Create the semantic.
2471 * of = high:bool((op1 ^ op2) & (op1 ^ regDst))
2472 */
2473 auto node = this->astCtxt->extract(bvSize-1, bvSize-1,
2474 this->astCtxt->bvand(
2475 this->astCtxt->bvxor(op1, op2),
2476 this->astCtxt->bvxor(op1, this->astCtxt->extract(high, low, this->astCtxt->reference(parent)))
2477 )
2478 );
2479
2480 /* Create the symbolic expression */
2481 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_OF), "Overflow flag");
2482
2483 /* Spread the taint from the parent to the child */
2484 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->setTaintRegister(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_OF), parent->isTainted);

2487
2488 void x86Semantics::pf_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst,
2489 const triton::engines::symbolic::SharedSymbolicExpression& parent,
2490 triton::arch::OperandWrapper& dst,
2491 bool vol) {
2492
2493 auto low = vol ? 0 : dst.getLow();
2494 auto high = vol ? triton::bitsize::byte-1 : !low ? triton::bitsize::byte-1 : triton::bitsize::word-1;
2495
2496 /*
2497 * Create the semantics.
2498 *
2499 * pf is set to one if there is an even number of bit set to 1 in the least
2500 * significant byte of the result.
2501 */
2502 auto node = this->astCtxt->bv(1, 1);
2503 for (triton::uint32 counter = 0; counter <= triton::bitsize::byte-1; counter++) {
2504 node = this->astCtxt->bvxor(
2505 node,
2506 this->astCtxt->extract(0, 0,
2507 this->astCtxt->bvlshr(
2508 this->astCtxt->extract(high, low, this->astCtxt->reference(parent)),
2509 this->astCtxt->bv(counter, triton::bitsize::byte)
2510 )
2511 )
2512 );
2513 }
2514
2515 /* Create the symbolic expression */
2516 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_PF), "Parity flag");
2517
2518 /* Spread the taint from the parent to the child */
2519 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->setTaintRegister(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_PF), parent->isTainted);
2520 }

2522
2523 void x86Semantics::pfShl_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst,
2524 const triton::engines::symbolic::SharedSymbolicExpression& parent,
2525 triton::arch::OperandWrapper& dst,
2526 const triton::ast::SharedAbstractNode& op2,
2527 bool vol) {
2528
2529 auto bvSize = dst.getBitSize();
2530 auto low = vol ? 0 : dst.getLow();
2531 auto high = vol ? triton::bitsize::byte-1 : !low ? triton::bitsize::byte-1 : triton::bitsize::word-1;
2532 auto pf = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_PF));
2533
2534 /*
2535 * Create the semantics.
2536 * pf if op2 != 0
2537 */
2538 auto node1 = this->astCtxt->bv(1, 1);
2539 for (triton::uint32 counter = 0; counter <= triton::bitsize::byte-1; counter++) {
2540 node1 = this->astCtxt->bvxor(
2541 node1,
2542 this->astCtxt->extract(0, 0,
2543 this->astCtxt->bvlshr(
2544 this->astCtxt->extract(high, low, this->astCtxt->reference(parent)),
2545 this->astCtxt->bv(counter, triton::bitsize::byte)
2546 )
2547 )
2548 );
2549 }
2550
2551 auto node2 = this->astCtxt->ite(
2552 this->astCtxt->equal(this->astCtxt->zx(bvSize - op2->getBitvectorSize(), op2), this->astCtxt->bv(0, bvSize)),
2553 this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(pf),
2554 node1
2555 );
2556
2557 /* Create the symbolic expression */
2558 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node2, pf.getConstRegister(), "Parity flag");
2559
2560 if (op2->evaluate()) {
2561 /* Spread the taint from the parent to the child */
2562 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->setTaintRegister(pf.getConstRegister(), parent->isTainted);
2563 }
2564 else {
2565 inst.removeWrittenRegister(pf.getConstRegister());
2566 }
2567 }

2805
2806 void x86Semantics::aaa_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
2807 auto src1 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_AL));
2808 auto src2 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_AH));
2809 auto src3 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_AF));
2810 auto dst = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_AX));
2811 auto dsttmp = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_AL));
2812
2813 /* Create symbolic operands */
2814 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src1);
2815 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src2);
2816 auto op3 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src3);
2817
2818 /* Create the semantics */
2819 auto node = this->astCtxt->ite(
2820 // if
2821 this->astCtxt->lor(
2822 this->astCtxt->bvugt(
2823 this->astCtxt->bvand(op1, this->astCtxt->bv(0xf, src1.getBitSize())),
2824 this->astCtxt->bv(9, src1.getBitSize())
2825 ),
2826 this->astCtxt->equal(op3, this->astCtxt->bvtrue())
2827 ),
2828 // then
2829 this->astCtxt->concat(
2830 this->astCtxt->bvadd(op2, this->astCtxt->bv(1, src2.getBitSize())),
2831 this->astCtxt->bvand(
2832 this->astCtxt->bvadd(op1, this->astCtxt->bv(6, src1.getBitSize())),
2833 this->astCtxt->bv(0xf, src1.getBitSize())
2834 )
2835 ),
2836 // else
2837 this->astCtxt->concat(
2838 op2,
2839 this->astCtxt->bvand(op1, this->astCtxt->bv(0xf, src1.getBitSize()))
2840 )
2841 );
2842
2843 /* Create symbolic expression */
2844 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, dst, "AAA operation");
2845
2846 /* Spread taint */
2847 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, dst);
2848
2849 /* Update symbolic flags */
2850 this->afAaa_s(inst, expr, dsttmp, op1, op3);
2851 this->cfAaa_s(inst, expr, dsttmp, op1, op3);
2852
2853 /* Tag undefined flags */
2854 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_OF));
2855 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_PF));
2856 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_SF));
2857 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_ZF));
2858
2859 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
2860 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
2861 }

2864 void x86Semantics::aad_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
2865 auto src1 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(triton::arch::Immediate(0x0a, triton::size::byte)); /* D5 0A */
2866 auto src2 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_AL));
2867 auto src3 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_AH));
2868 auto dst = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_AX));
2869 auto dsttmp = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_AL));
2870
2871 /* D5 ib */
2872 if (inst.operands.size() == 1)
2873 src1 = inst.operands[0];
2874
2875 /* Create symbolic operands */
2876 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src1);
2877 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src2);
2878 auto op3 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src3);
2879
2880 /* Create the semantics */
2881 auto node = this->astCtxt->zx(
2882 triton::bitsize::byte,
2883 this->astCtxt->bvadd(
2884 op2,
2885 this->astCtxt->bvmul(op3, op1)
2886 )
2887 );
2888
2889 /* Create symbolic expression */
2890 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, dst, "AAD operation");
2891
2892 /* Spread taint */
2893 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, dst);
2894
2895 /* Update symbolic flags */
2896 this->pf_s(inst, expr, dsttmp);
2897 this->sf_s(inst, expr, dsttmp);
2898 this->zf_s(inst, expr, dsttmp);
2899
2900 /* Tag undefined flags */
2901 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_AF));
2902 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_CF));
2903 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_OF));
2904
2905 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
2906 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
2907 }

2977 this->astCtxt->bvsub(op1, this->astCtxt->bv(6, src1.getBitSize())),
2978 this->astCtxt->bv(0xf, src1.getBitSize())
2979 )
2980 ),
2981 // else
2982 this->astCtxt->concat(
2983 op2,
2984 this->astCtxt->bvand(op1, this->astCtxt->bv(0xf, src1.getBitSize()))
2985 )
2986 );
2987
2988 /* Create symbolic expression */
2989 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, dst, "AAS operation");
2990
2991 /* Spread taint */
2992 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, dst);
2993
2994 /* Update symbolic flags */
2995 this->afAaa_s(inst, expr, dsttmp, op1, op3);
2996 this->cfAaa_s(inst, expr, dsttmp, op1, op3);

2999 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_OF));
3000 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_PF));

3009 void x86Semantics::adc_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
3010 auto& dst = inst.operands[0];
3011 auto& src = inst.operands[1];

3034 this->sf_s(inst, expr, dst);
3035 this->zf_s(inst, expr, dst);
3036
3037 /* Update the symbolic control flow */

3383 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src);
3384

3387 switch (src.getSize()) {
3388 case triton::size::byte:
3389 node = this->astCtxt->ite(
3390 this->astCtxt->equal(op2, this->astCtxt->bv(0, bvSize2)), /* Apply BSF only if op2 != 0 */
3391 op1,
3392 this->astCtxt->ite(this->astCtxt->equal(this->astCtxt->extract(0, 0, op2), this->astCtxt->bvtrue()), this->astCtxt->bv(0, bvSize1),
3393 this->astCtxt->ite(this->astCtxt->equal(this->astCtxt->extract(1, 1, op2), this->astCtxt->bvtrue()), this->astCtxt->bv(1, bvSize1),
3394 this->astCtxt->ite(this->astCtxt->equal(this->astCtxt->extract(2, 2, op2), this->astCtxt->bvtrue()), this->astCtxt->bv(2, bvSize1),
3395 this->astCtxt->ite(this->astCtxt->equal(this->astCtxt->extract(3, 3, op2), this->astCtxt->bvtrue()), this->astCtxt->bv(3, bvSize1),
3396 this->astCtxt->ite(this->astCtxt->equal(this->astCtxt->extract(4, 4, op2), this->astCtxt->bvtrue()), this->astCtxt->bv(4, bvSize1),
3397 this->astCtxt->ite(this->astCtxt->equal(this->astCtxt->extract(5, 5, op2), this->astCtxt->bvtrue()), this->astCtxt->bv(5, bvSize1),
3398 this->astCtxt->ite(this->astCtxt->equal(this->astCtxt->extract(6, 6, op2), this->astCtxt->bvtrue()), this->astCtxt->bv(6, bvSize1),
3399 this->astCtxt->ite(this->astCtxt->equal(this->astCtxt->extract(7, 7, op2), this->astCtxt->bvtrue()), this->astCtxt->bv(7, bvSize1),
3400 this->astCtxt->bv(0, bvSize1)
3401 ))))))))
3402 );
3403 break;

3526 this->astCtxt->ite(this->astCtxt->equal(this->astCtxt->extract(54, 54, op2), this->astCtxt->bvtrue()), this->astCtxt->bv(54, bvSize1),
3527 this->astCtxt->ite(this->astCtxt->equal(this->astCtxt->extract(55, 55, op2), this->astCtxt->bvtrue()), this->astCtxt->bv(55, bvSize1),
3528 this->astCtxt->ite(this->astCtxt->equal(this->astCtxt->extract(56, 56, op2), this->astCtxt->bvtrue()), this->astCtxt->bv(56, bvSize1),

3531 this->astCtxt->ite(this->astCtxt->equal(this->astCtxt->extract(59, 59, op2), this->astCtxt->bvtrue()), this->astCtxt->bv(59, bvSize1),
3532 this->astCtxt->ite(this->astCtxt->equal(this->astCtxt->extract(60, 60, op2), this->astCtxt->bvtrue()), this->astCtxt->bv(60, bvSize1),

3535 this->astCtxt->ite(this->astCtxt->equal(this->astCtxt->extract(63, 63, op2), this->astCtxt->bvtrue()), this->astCtxt->bv(63, bvSize1),
3536 this->astCtxt->bv(0, bvSize1)
3537 ))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))
3538 );

3540 default:
3541 throw triton::exceptions::Semantics("x86Semantics::bsf_s(): Invalid operand size.");
3542 }
3543
3544 /* Create symbolic expression */
3545 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, dst, "BSF operation");
3546
3547 /* Spread taint */
3548 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintAssignment(dst, src);
3549
3550 /* Update symbolic flags */
3551 this->zfBsf_s(inst, expr, src, op2);
3552
3553 /* Tag undefined flags */
3554 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_AF));
3555 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_CF));
3556 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_OF));
3557 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_PF));
3558 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_SF));
3559
3560 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
3561 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
3562 }
3563
3564
3565 void x86Semantics::bsr_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
3566 auto& dst = inst.operands[0];
3567 auto& src = inst.operands[1];
3568 auto bvSize1 = dst.getBitSize();
3569 auto bvSize2 = src.getBitSize();
3570
3571 /* Create symbolic operands */
3572 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, dst);
3573 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src);
3574
3575 /* Create the semantics */
3576 triton::ast::SharedAbstractNode node = nullptr;

3726 this->astCtxt->bv(0, bvSize1)
3727 ))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))
3728 );
3729 break;
3730 default:
3731 throw triton::exceptions::Semantics("x86Semantics::bsr_s(): Invalid operand size.");
3732 }
3733
3734 /* Create symbolic expression */
3735 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, dst, "BSR operation");
3736
3737 /* Spread taint */
3738 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintAssignment(dst, src);
3739
3740 /* Update symbolic flags */
3741 this->zfBsf_s(inst, expr, src, op2); /* same as bsf */
3742
3743 /* Tag undefined flags */
3744 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_AF));
3745 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_CF));
3746 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_OF));
3747 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_PF));
3748 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_SF));
3749
3750 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
3751 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
3752 }
3753
3754
3755 void x86Semantics::bswap_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
3756 auto& src = inst.operands[0];
3757
3758 /* Create symbolic operands */
3759 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src);
3760
3761 /* Create the semantics */
3762 std::list<triton::ast::SharedAbstractNode> bytes;
3763 switch (src.getSize()) {
3764 case triton::size::qword:
3765 bytes.push_front(this->astCtxt->extract(63, 56, op1));
3766 bytes.push_front(this->astCtxt->extract(55, 48, op1));
3767 bytes.push_front(this->astCtxt->extract(47, 40, op1));
3768 bytes.push_front(this->astCtxt->extract(39, 32, op1));
3769 case triton::size::dword:
3770 bytes.push_front(this->astCtxt->extract(31, 24, op1));
3771 bytes.push_front(this->astCtxt->extract(23, 16, op1));
3772 case triton::size::word:
3773 // See #1131
3774 bytes.push_front(this->astCtxt->bv(0, 8));
3775 bytes.push_front(this->astCtxt->bv(0, 8));
3776 break;
3777 default:
3778 throw triton::exceptions::Semantics("x86Semantics::bswap_s(): Invalid operand size.");
3779 }
3780
3781 auto node = this->astCtxt->concat(bytes);
3782
3783 /* Create symbolic expression */
3784 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, src, "BSWAP operation");
3785
3786 /* Spread taint */
3787 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintAssignment(src, src);
3788
3789 /* Tag undefined registers */
3790 if (src.getSize() == triton::size::word) {
3791 // When the BSWAP instruction references a 16-bit register, the result is undefined.
3792 this->undefined_s(inst, src.getRegister());
3793 }
3794
3795 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
3796 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
3797 }
3798
3799
3800 void x86Semantics::bt_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
3801 auto dst = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_CF));
3802 auto& src1 = inst.operands[0];
3803 auto& src2 = inst.operands[1];
3804
3805 /* Create symbolic operands */
3806 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src1);
3807 auto op2 = this->astCtxt->zx(src1.getBitSize() - src2.getBitSize(), this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src2));
3808
3809 /* Create the semantics */
3810 auto node = this->astCtxt->extract(0, 0,
3811 this->astCtxt->bvlshr(
3812 op1,
3813 this->astCtxt->bvsmod(
3814 op2,
3815 this->astCtxt->bv(src1.getBitSize(), src1.getBitSize())
3816 )
3817 )
3818 );
3819
3820 /* Create symbolic expression */
3821 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_CF), "BT operation");
3822
3823 /* Spread taint */
3824 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src1);
3825 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src2);
3826
3827 /* Tag undefined flags */
3828 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_AF));
3829 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_OF));
3830 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_PF));
3831 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_SF));
3832
3833 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
3834 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
3835 }

3838 void x86Semantics::btc_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
3839 auto dst1 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_CF));
3840 auto& dst2 = inst.operands[0];
3841 auto& src1 = inst.operands[1];
3842
3843 /* Create symbolic operands */
3844 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, dst2);
3845 auto op2 = this->astCtxt->zx(dst2.getBitSize() - src1.getBitSize(), this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src1));
3846
3847 /* Create the semantics */
3848 auto node1 = this->astCtxt->extract(0, 0,
3849 this->astCtxt->bvlshr(
3850 op1,
3851 this->astCtxt->bvsmod(
3852 op2,
3853 this->astCtxt->bv(dst2.getBitSize(), dst2.getBitSize())
3854 )
3855 )
3856 );
3857 auto node2 = this->astCtxt->ite(
3858 this->astCtxt->equal(node1, this->astCtxt->bvfalse()),
3859 /* BTS */
3860 this->astCtxt->bvor(
3861 op1,
3862 this->astCtxt->bvshl(
3863 this->astCtxt->bv(1, dst2.getBitSize()),
3864 this->astCtxt->bvsmod(
3865 op2,
3866 this->astCtxt->bv(dst2.getBitSize(), dst2.getBitSize())
3867 )
3868 )
3869 ),
3870 /* BTR */
3871 this->astCtxt->bvand(
3872 op1,
3873 this->astCtxt->bvsub(
3874 op1,
3875 this->astCtxt->bvshl(
3876 this->astCtxt->bv(1, dst2.getBitSize()),
3877 this->astCtxt->bvsmod(
3878 op2,
3879 this->astCtxt->bv(dst2.getBitSize(), dst2.getBitSize())
3880 )
3881 )
3882 )
3883 )
3884 );
3885
3886 /* Create symbolic expression */
3887 auto expr1 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node1, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_CF), "BTC carry operation");
3888 auto expr2 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node2, dst2, "BTC complement operation");
3889
3890 /* Spread taint */
3891 expr1->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst1, dst2);
3892 expr1->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst1, src1);
3893 expr2->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst2, src1);
3894
3895 /* Tag undefined flags */
3896 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_AF));
3897 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_OF));
3898 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_PF));
3899 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_SF));
3900
3901 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
3902 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
3903 }

4012
4013 void x86Semantics::call_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
4014 auto stack = this->architecture->getStackPointer();
4015
4016 /* Create the semantics - side effect */
4017 auto stackValue = alignSubStack_s(inst, stack.getSize());
4018 auto pc = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getProgramCounter());
4019 auto sp = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(triton::arch::MemoryAccess(stackValue, stack.getSize()));
4020 auto& src = inst.operands[0];
4021
4022 /* Create symbolic operands */
4023 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src);
4024
4025 /* Create the semantics - side effect */
4026 auto node1 = this->astCtxt->bv(inst.getNextAddress(), pc.getBitSize());
4027
4028 /* Create the semantics */
4029 auto node2 = op1;
4030
4031 /* Create the symbolic expression */
4032 auto expr1 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node1, sp, "Saved Program Counter");
4033
4034 /* Create symbolic expression */
4035 auto expr2 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node2, pc, "Program Counter");
4036
4037 /* Spread taint */
4038 expr1->isTainted = this->taintEngine->untaintMemory(sp.getMemory());
4039 expr2->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintAssignment(pc, src);
4040
4041 /* Create the path constraint */
4042 this->symbolicEngine->pushPathConstraint(inst, expr2);
4043 }

4066 void x86Semantics::cdq_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
4067 auto dst = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_EDX));
4068 auto src = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_EAX));
4069
4070 /* Create symbolic operands */
4071 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src);
4072
4073 /* Create the semantics - TMP = 64 bitvec (EDX:EAX) */
4074 auto node1 = this->astCtxt->sx(triton::bitsize::dword, op1);
4075
4076 /* Create symbolic expression */
4077 auto expr1 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicVolatileExpression(inst, node1, "Temporary variable");
4078
4079 /* Spread taint */
4080 expr1->isTainted = this->taintEngine->isRegisterTainted(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_EAX));
4081
4082 /* Create the semantics - EDX = TMP[63...32] */
4083 auto node2 = this->astCtxt->extract(triton::bitsize::qword-1, triton::bitsize::dword, this->astCtxt->reference(expr1));
4084
4085 /* Create symbolic expression */
4086 auto expr2 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node2, dst, "CDQ operation");
4087
4088 /* Spread taint */
4089 expr2->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintAssignment(dst, src);
4090
4091 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
4092 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
4093 }

4136 void x86Semantics::clts_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
4137 auto dst = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_CR0));
4138
4139 /* Create symbolic operands */
4140 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, dst);
4141
4142 /* Create the semantics */
4143 triton::ast::SharedAbstractNode node = nullptr;
4144
4145 switch (dst.getBitSize()) {
4146 case triton::bitsize::qword:
4147 node = this->astCtxt->bvand(op1, this->astCtxt->bv(0xfffffffffffffff7, triton::bitsize::qword));
4148 break;
4149 case triton::bitsize::dword:
4150 node = this->astCtxt->bvand(op1, this->astCtxt->bv(0xfffffff7, triton::bitsize::dword));
4151 break;
4152 default:
4153 throw triton::exceptions::Semantics("x86Semantics::clts_s(): Invalid operand size.");
4154 }
4155
4156 /* Create symbolic expression */
4157 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, dst, "CLTS operation");
4158
4159 /* Spread taint */
4160 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, dst);
4161
4162 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
4163 this->controlFlow_s(inst);

4193
4194 void x86Semantics::cmova_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
4195 auto& dst = inst.operands[0];
4196 auto& src = inst.operands[1];
4197 auto cf = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_CF));
4198 auto zf = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_ZF));
4199
4200 /* Create symbolic operands */
4201 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, dst);
4202 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src);
4203 auto op3 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, cf);
4204 auto op4 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, zf);
4205
4206 /* Create the semantics */
4207 auto node = this->astCtxt->ite(this->astCtxt->equal(this->astCtxt->bvand(this->astCtxt->bvnot(op3), this->astCtxt->bvnot(op4)), this->astCtxt->bvtrue()), op2, op1);
4208
4209 /* Create symbolic expression */
4210 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, dst, "CMOVA operation");
4211
4212 /* Spread taint and condition flag */
4213 if (op3->evaluate().is_zero() && op4->evaluate().is_zero()) {
4214 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintAssignment(dst, src);
4215 inst.setConditionTaken(true);
4216 }
4217 else {
4218 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, dst);
4219 }
4220
4221 expr->isTainted |= this->taintEngine->isTainted(cf) || this->taintEngine->isTainted(zf);
4222
4223 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
4224 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
4225 }

4291
4292 void x86Semantics::cmovbe_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
4293 auto& dst = inst.operands[0];
4294 auto& src = inst.operands[1];
4295 auto cf = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_CF));
4296 auto zf = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_ZF));
4297
4298 /* Create symbolic operands */
4299 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, dst);
4300 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src);
4301 auto op3 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, cf);
4302 auto op4 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, zf);
4303
4304 /* Create the semantics */
4305 auto node = this->astCtxt->ite(this->astCtxt->equal(this->astCtxt->bvor(op3, op4), this->astCtxt->bvtrue()), op2, op1);
4306
4307 /* Create symbolic expression */
4308 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, dst, "CMOVBE operation");
4309
4310 /* Spread taint and condition flag */
4311 if (!op3->evaluate().is_zero() || !op4->evaluate().is_zero()) {
4312 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintAssignment(dst, src);
4313 inst.setConditionTaken(true);
4314 }
4315 else {
4316 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, dst);
4317 }
4318
4319 expr->isTainted |= this->taintEngine->isTainted(cf) || this->taintEngine->isTainted(zf);
4320
4321 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
4322 this->controlFlow_s(inst);

4326 void x86Semantics::cmove_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
4327 auto& dst = inst.operands[0];
4328 auto& src = inst.operands[1];
4329 auto zf = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_ZF));
4330
4331 /* Create symbolic operands */

4333 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src);
4334 auto op3 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, zf);
4335

4339 /* Create symbolic expression */

4349 }

4722
4723 void x86Semantics::cmp_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
4724 auto& dst = inst.operands[0];
4725 auto& src = inst.operands[1];
4726
4727 /* Create symbolic operands */
4728 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, dst);
4729 auto op2 = this->astCtxt->sx(dst.getBitSize() - src.getBitSize(), this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src));
4730
4731 /* Create the semantics */
4732 auto node = this->astCtxt->bvsub(op1, op2);
4733
4734 /* Create symbolic expression */
4735 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicVolatileExpression(inst, node, "CMP operation");
4736
4737 /* Spread taint */
4738 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->isTainted(dst) | this->taintEngine->isTainted(src);
4739
4740 /* Update symbolic flags */
4741 this->af_s(inst, expr, dst, op1, op2, true);
4742 this->cfSub_s(inst, expr, dst, op1, op2, true);
4743 this->ofSub_s(inst, expr, dst, op1, op2, true);
4744 this->pf_s(inst, expr, dst, true);
4745 this->sf_s(inst, expr, dst, true);
4746 this->zf_s(inst, expr, dst, true);
4747
4748 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
4749 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
4750 }
4751
4752
4753 void x86Semantics::cmpsb_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
4754 auto& dst = inst.operands[0];
4755 auto& src = inst.operands[1];
4756 auto index1 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getParentRegister(ID_REG_X86_SI));
4757 auto index2 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getParentRegister(ID_REG_X86_DI));
4758 auto cx = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getParentRegister(ID_REG_X86_CX));
4759 auto df = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_DF));
4760
4761 /* If the REP prefix is defined, convert REP into REPE */
4762 if (inst.getPrefix() == triton::arch::x86::ID_PREFIX_REP)
4763 inst.setPrefix(triton::arch::x86::ID_PREFIX_REPE);
4764
4765 /* Check if there is a REP prefix and a counter to zero */
4766 if (inst.getPrefix() != triton::arch::x86::ID_PREFIX_INVALID && this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(cx)->evaluate().is_zero()) {
4767 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
4768 return;
4769 }
4770
4771 /* Create symbolic operands */
4772 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, dst);
4773 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src);
4774 auto op3 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, index1);
4775 auto op4 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, index2);
4776 auto op5 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, df);
4777
4778 /* Create the semantics */
4779 auto node1 = this->astCtxt->bvsub(op1, op2);
4780 auto node2 = this->astCtxt->ite(
4781 this->astCtxt->equal(op5, this->astCtxt->bvfalse()),
4782 this->astCtxt->bvadd(op3, this->astCtxt->bv(triton::size::byte, index1.getBitSize())),
4783 this->astCtxt->bvsub(op3, this->astCtxt->bv(triton::size::byte, index1.getBitSize()))
4784 );
4785 auto node3 = this->astCtxt->ite(
4786 this->astCtxt->equal(op5, this->astCtxt->bvfalse()),
4787 this->astCtxt->bvadd(op4, this->astCtxt->bv(triton::size::byte, index2.getBitSize())),
4788 this->astCtxt->bvsub(op4, this->astCtxt->bv(triton::size::byte, index2.getBitSize()))
4789 );
4790
4791 /* Create symbolic expression */
4792 auto expr1 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicVolatileExpression(inst, node1, "CMPSB operation");
4793 auto expr2 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node2, index1, "Index (SI) operation");
4794 auto expr3 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node3, index2, "Index (DI) operation");
4795
4796 /* Spread taint */
4797 expr1->isTainted = this->taintEngine->isTainted(dst) | this->taintEngine->isTainted(src);
4798 expr2->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(index1, index1);
4799 expr3->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(index2, index2);
4800
4801 /* Update symbolic flags */
4802 this->af_s(inst, expr1, dst, op1, op2, true);
4803 this->cfSub_s(inst, expr1, dst, op1, op2, true);
4804 this->ofSub_s(inst, expr1, dst, op1, op2, true);
4805 this->pf_s(inst, expr1, dst, true);
4806 this->sf_s(inst, expr1, dst, true);
4807 this->zf_s(inst, expr1, dst, true);
4808
4809 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
4810 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
4811 }
4812
4813
4814 void x86Semantics::cmpsd_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
4815 auto& dst = inst.operands[0];
4816 auto& src = inst.operands[1];
4817 auto index1 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getParentRegister(ID_REG_X86_SI));
4818 auto index2 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getParentRegister(ID_REG_X86_DI));
4819 auto cx = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getParentRegister(ID_REG_X86_CX));
4820 auto df = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_DF));
4821
4822 /* If the REP prefix is defined, convert REP into REPE */
4823 if (inst.getPrefix() == triton::arch::x86::ID_PREFIX_REP)
4824 inst.setPrefix(triton::arch::x86::ID_PREFIX_REPE);
4825
4826 /* Check if there is a REP prefix and a counter to zero */
4827 if (inst.getPrefix() != triton::arch::x86::ID_PREFIX_INVALID && this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(cx)->evaluate().is_zero()) {
4828 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
4829 return;
4830 }
4831
4832 /* Create symbolic operands */
4833 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, dst);
4834 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src);
4835 auto op3 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, index1);
4836 auto op4 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, index2);
4837 auto op5 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, df);
4838
4839 /* Create the semantics */
4840 auto node1 = this->astCtxt->bvsub(op1, op2);
4841 auto node2 = this->astCtxt->ite(
4842 this->astCtxt->equal(op5, this->astCtxt->bvfalse()),
4843 this->astCtxt->bvadd(op3, this->astCtxt->bv(triton::size::dword, index1.getBitSize())),
4844 this->astCtxt->bvsub(op3, this->astCtxt->bv(triton::size::dword, index1.getBitSize()))
4845 );
4846 auto node3 = this->astCtxt->ite(
4847 this->astCtxt->equal(op5, this->astCtxt->bvfalse()),
4848 this->astCtxt->bvadd(op4, this->astCtxt->bv(triton::size::dword, index2.getBitSize())),
4849 this->astCtxt->bvsub(op4, this->astCtxt->bv(triton::size::dword, index2.getBitSize()))
4850 );
4851
4852 /* Create symbolic expression */
4853 auto expr1 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicVolatileExpression(inst, node1, "CMPSD operation");
4854 auto expr2 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node2, index1, "Index (SI) operation");
4855 auto expr3 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node3, index2, "Index (DI) operation");
4856
4857 /* Spread taint */
4858 expr1->isTainted = this->taintEngine->isTainted(dst) | this->taintEngine->isTainted(src);
4859 expr2->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(index1, index1);
4860 expr3->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(index2, index2);
4861
4862 /* Update symbolic flags */
4863 this->af_s(inst, expr1, dst, op1, op2, true);
4864 this->cfSub_s(inst, expr1, dst, op1, op2, true);
4865 this->ofSub_s(inst, expr1, dst, op1, op2, true);
4866 this->pf_s(inst, expr1, dst, true);
4867 this->sf_s(inst, expr1, dst, true);
4868 this->zf_s(inst, expr1, dst, true);
4869
4870 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
4871 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
4872 }

4874
4875 void x86Semantics::cmpsq_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
4876 auto& dst = inst.operands[0];
4877 auto& src = inst.operands[1];
4878 auto index1 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getParentRegister(ID_REG_X86_SI));
4879 auto index2 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getParentRegister(ID_REG_X86_DI));
4880 auto cx = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getParentRegister(ID_REG_X86_CX));
4881 auto df = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_DF));
4882
4883 /* If the REP prefix is defined, convert REP into REPE */
4884 if (inst.getPrefix() == triton::arch::x86::ID_PREFIX_REP)
4885 inst.setPrefix(triton::arch::x86::ID_PREFIX_REPE);
4886
4887 /* Check if there is a REP prefix and a counter to zero */
4888 if (inst.getPrefix() != triton::arch::x86::ID_PREFIX_INVALID && this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(cx)->evaluate().is_zero()) {
4889 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
4890 return;
4891 }
4892
4893 /* Create symbolic operands */
4894 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, dst);
4895 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src);
4896 auto op3 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, index1);
4897 auto op4 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, index2);
4898 auto op5 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, df);
4899
4900 /* Create the semantics */
4901 auto node1 = this->astCtxt->bvsub(op1, op2);
4902 auto node2 = this->astCtxt->ite(
4903 this->astCtxt->equal(op5, this->astCtxt->bvfalse()),
4904 this->astCtxt->bvadd(op3, this->astCtxt->bv(triton::size::qword, index1.getBitSize())),
4905 this->astCtxt->bvsub(op3, this->astCtxt->bv(triton::size::qword, index1.getBitSize()))
4906 );
4907 auto node3 = this->astCtxt->ite(
4908 this->astCtxt->equal(op5, this->astCtxt->bvfalse()),
4909 this->astCtxt->bvadd(op4, this->astCtxt->bv(triton::size::qword, index2.getBitSize())),
4910 this->astCtxt->bvsub(op4, this->astCtxt->bv(triton::size::qword, index2.getBitSize()))
4911 );
4912
4913 /* Create symbolic expression */
4914 auto expr1 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicVolatileExpression(inst, node1, "CMPSQ operation");
4915 auto expr2 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node2, index1, "Index (SI) operation");
4916 auto expr3 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node3, index2, "Index (DI) operation");
4917
4918 /* Spread taint */
4919 expr1->isTainted = this->taintEngine->isTainted(dst) | this->taintEngine->isTainted(src);
4920 expr2->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(index1, index1);
4921 expr3->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(index2, index2);
4922
4923 /* Update symbolic flags */
4924 this->af_s(inst, expr1, dst, op1, op2, true);
4925 this->cfSub_s(inst, expr1, dst, op1, op2, true);
4926 this->ofSub_s(inst, expr1, dst, op1, op2, true);
4927 this->pf_s(inst, expr1, dst, true);
4928 this->sf_s(inst, expr1, dst, true);
4929 this->zf_s(inst, expr1, dst, true);
4930
4931 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
4932 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
4933 }
