13200 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src);
13201
13202 /* Create the semantics */
13203 std::vector<triton::ast::SharedAbstractNode> packed;
13204 packed.reserve(8);
13205
13206 switch (dst.getBitSize()) {
13207
13208 /* XMM */
13209 case triton::bitsize::dqword:
13210 packed.push_back(this->astCtxt->bvsub(this->astCtxt->extract(127, 112, op1), this->astCtxt->extract(127, 112, op2)));
13211 packed.push_back(this->astCtxt->bvsub(this->astCtxt->extract(111, 96, op1), this->astCtxt->extract(111, 96, op2)));
13212 packed.push_back(this->astCtxt->bvsub(this->astCtxt->extract(95, 80, op1), this->astCtxt->extract(95, 80, op2)));
13213 packed.push_back(this->astCtxt->bvsub(this->astCtxt->extract(79, 64, op1), this->astCtxt->extract(79, 64, op2)));
13214
13215 /* MMX */
13216 case triton::bitsize::qword:
13217 packed.push_back(this->astCtxt->bvsub(this->astCtxt->extract(63, 48, op1), this->astCtxt->extract(63, 48, op2)));
13218 packed.push_back(this->astCtxt->bvsub(this->astCtxt->extract(47, 32, op1), this->astCtxt->extract(47, 32, op2)));
13219 packed.push_back(this->astCtxt->bvsub(this->astCtxt->extract(31, 16, op1), this->astCtxt->extract(31, 16, op2)));
13220 packed.push_back(this->astCtxt->bvsub(this->astCtxt->extract(15, 0, op1), this->astCtxt->extract(15, 0, op2)));
13221 break;
13222
13223 default:
13224 throw triton::exceptions::Semantics("x86Semantics::psubw_s(): Invalid operand size.");
13225
13226 }
13227
13228 auto node = this->astCtxt->concat(packed);
13229
13230 /* Create symbolic expression */
13231 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, dst, "PSUBW operation");
13232
13233 /* Update the x87 FPU Tag Word */
13234 if (dst.getBitSize() == triton::bitsize::qword) {
13235 this->updateFTW(inst, expr);
13236 }
13237
13238 /* Spread taint */
13239 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src);
13240
13241 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
13242 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
13243 }
13244
13245
13246 void x86Semantics::ptest_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
13247 auto& src1 = inst.operands[0];
13248 auto& src2 = inst.operands[1];
13249
13250 /* Create symbolic operands */
13251 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src1);
13252 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src2);
13253
13254 /* Create the semantics */
13255 auto node1 = this->astCtxt->bvand(op1, op2);
13256 auto node2 = this->astCtxt->bvand(op1, this->astCtxt->bvnot(op2));
13257
13258 /* Create symbolic expression */
13259 auto expr1 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicVolatileExpression(inst, node1, "PTEST operation");
13260 auto expr2 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicVolatileExpression(inst, node2, "PTEST operation");
13261
13262 /* Spread taint */
13263 expr1->isTainted = this->taintEngine->isTainted(src1) | this->taintEngine->isTainted(src2);
13264 expr2->isTainted = this->taintEngine->isTainted(src1) | this->taintEngine->isTainted(src2);
13265
13266 /* Update symbolic flags */
13267 this->clearFlag_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_AF), "Clears adjust flag");
13268 this->cfPtest_s(inst, expr2, src1, true);
13269 this->clearFlag_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_OF), "Clears overflow flag");
13270 this->clearFlag_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_PF), "Clears parity flag");
13271 this->clearFlag_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_SF), "Clears sign flag");
13272 this->zf_s(inst, expr1, src1, true);
13273
13274 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
13275 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
13276 }

13313 unpack.push_back(this->astCtxt->extract(103, 96, op2));
13314 unpack.push_back(this->astCtxt->extract(103, 96, op1));
13315 unpack.push_back(this->astCtxt->extract(95, 88, op2));

13320 unpack.push_back(this->astCtxt->extract(79, 72, op1));
13321 unpack.push_back(this->astCtxt->extract(71, 64, op2));
13322 unpack.push_back(this->astCtxt->extract(71, 64, op1));

13700
13701 void x86Semantics::push_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
13702 auto& src = inst.operands[0];
13703 auto stack = this->architecture->getStackPointer();
13704 triton::uint32 size = stack.getSize();
13705
13706 /* If it's an immediate source, the memory access is always based on the arch size */
13707 if (src.getType() != triton::arch::OP_IMM)
13708 size = src.getSize();
13709
13710 /* Create symbolic operands */
13711 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src);
13712
13713 /* Create the semantics - side effect */
13714 auto stackValue = alignSubStack_s(inst, size);
13715 auto dst = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(triton::arch::MemoryAccess(stackValue, size));
13716
13717 /* Create the semantics */
13718 auto node = this->astCtxt->zx(dst.getBitSize() - src.getBitSize(), op1);
13719
13720 /* Create symbolic expression */
13721 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, dst, "PUSH operation");
13722
13723 /* Spread taint */
13724 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintAssignment(dst, src);
13725
13726 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
13727 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
13728 }
13729
13730
13731 void x86Semantics::pushal_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
13732 auto stack = this->architecture->getStackPointer();
13733 auto stackValue = static_cast<triton::uint64>(this->architecture->getConcreteRegisterValue(stack));
13734 auto dst1 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(triton::arch::MemoryAccess(stackValue-(stack.getSize() * 1), stack.getSize()));
13735 auto dst2 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(triton::arch::MemoryAccess(stackValue-(stack.getSize() * 2), stack.getSize()));
13736 auto dst3 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(triton::arch::MemoryAccess(stackValue-(stack.getSize() * 3), stack.getSize()));
13737 auto dst4 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(triton::arch::MemoryAccess(stackValue-(stack.getSize() * 4), stack.getSize()));
13738 auto dst5 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(triton::arch::MemoryAccess(stackValue-(stack.getSize() * 5), stack.getSize()));
13739 auto dst6 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(triton::arch::MemoryAccess(stackValue-(stack.getSize() * 6), stack.getSize()));
13740 auto dst7 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(triton::arch::MemoryAccess(stackValue-(stack.getSize() * 7), stack.getSize()));
13741 auto dst8 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(triton::arch::MemoryAccess(stackValue-(stack.getSize() * 8), stack.getSize()));
13742 auto src1 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_EAX));
13743 auto src2 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_ECX));
13744 auto src3 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_EDX));
13745 auto src4 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_EBX));
13746 auto src5 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_ESP));
13747 auto src6 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_EBP));
13748 auto src7 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_ESI));
13749 auto src8 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_EDI));
13750
13751 /* Create symbolic operands */
13752 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src1);
13753 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src2);
13754 auto op3 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src3);
13755 auto op4 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src4);
13756 auto op5 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src5);
13757 auto op6 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src6);
13758 auto op7 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src7);
13759 auto op8 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src8);
13760
13761 /* Create the semantics */
13762 auto node1 = this->astCtxt->zx(dst1.getBitSize() - src1.getBitSize(), op1);
13763 auto node2 = this->astCtxt->zx(dst2.getBitSize() - src2.getBitSize(), op2);
13764 auto node3 = this->astCtxt->zx(dst3.getBitSize() - src3.getBitSize(), op3);
13765 auto node4 = this->astCtxt->zx(dst4.getBitSize() - src4.getBitSize(), op4);
13766 auto node5 = this->astCtxt->zx(dst5.getBitSize() - src5.getBitSize(), op5);
13767 auto node6 = this->astCtxt->zx(dst6.getBitSize() - src6.getBitSize(), op6);
13768 auto node7 = this->astCtxt->zx(dst7.getBitSize() - src7.getBitSize(), op7);
13769 auto node8 = this->astCtxt->zx(dst8.getBitSize() - src8.getBitSize(), op8);
13770
13771 /* Create symbolic expression */
13772 alignSubStack_s(inst, 32);
13773 auto expr1 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node1, dst1, "PUSHAL EAX operation");
13774 auto expr2 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node2, dst2, "PUSHAL ECX operation");
13775 auto expr3 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node3, dst3, "PUSHAL EDX operation");
13776 auto expr4 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node4, dst4, "PUSHAL EBX operation");
13777 auto expr5 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node5, dst5, "PUSHAL ESP operation");
13778 auto expr6 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node6, dst6, "PUSHAL EBP operation");
13779 auto expr7 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node7, dst7, "PUSHAL ESI operation");
13780 auto expr8 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node8, dst8, "PUSHAL EDI operation");
13781
13782 /* Spread taint */
13783 expr1->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintAssignment(dst1, src1);
13784 expr2->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintAssignment(dst2, src2);
13785 expr3->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintAssignment(dst3, src3);
13786 expr4->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintAssignment(dst4, src4);
13787 expr5->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintAssignment(dst5, src5);
13788 expr6->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintAssignment(dst6, src6);
13789 expr7->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintAssignment(dst7, src7);
13790 expr8->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintAssignment(dst8, src8);
13791
13792 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
13793 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
13794 }

13797 void x86Semantics::pushfd_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
13798 auto stack = this->architecture->getStackPointer();
13799
13800 /* Create the semantics - side effect */
13801 auto stackValue = alignSubStack_s(inst, stack.getSize());
13802 auto dst = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(triton::arch::MemoryAccess(stackValue, stack.getSize()));
13803 auto src1 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_CF));
13804 auto src2 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_PF));
13805 auto src3 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_AF));
13806 auto src4 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_ZF));
13807 auto src5 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_SF));
13808 auto src6 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_TF));
13809 auto src7 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_IF));
13810 auto src8 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_DF));
13811 auto src9 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_OF));
13812 auto src10 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_NT));
13813 auto src11 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_AC));
13814 auto src12 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_VIF));
13815 auto src13 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_VIP));
13816 auto src14 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_ID));
13817
13818 /* Create symbolic operands */
13819 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src1);
13820 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src2);
13821 auto op3 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src3);
13822 auto op4 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src4);
13823 auto op5 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src5);
13824 auto op6 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src6);
13825 auto op7 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src7);
13826 auto op8 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src8);
13827 auto op9 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src9);
13828 auto op10 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src10);
13829 auto op11 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src11);
13830 auto op12 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src12);
13831 auto op13 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src13);
13832 auto op14 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src14);
13833
13834 /* Create the semantics */
13835 std::vector<triton::ast::SharedAbstractNode> eflags;
13836 eflags.reserve(22);
13837
13838 eflags.push_back(op14);
13839 eflags.push_back(op13);
13840 eflags.push_back(op12);
13841 eflags.push_back(op11);
13842 eflags.push_back(this->astCtxt->bvfalse()); /* vm */
13843 eflags.push_back(this->astCtxt->bvfalse()); /* rf */
13844 eflags.push_back(this->astCtxt->bvfalse()); /* Reserved */
13845 eflags.push_back(op10);
13846 eflags.push_back(this->astCtxt->bvfalse()); /* iopl */
13847 eflags.push_back(this->astCtxt->bvfalse()); /* iopl */
13848 eflags.push_back(op9);
13849 eflags.push_back(op8);
13850 eflags.push_back(op7);
13851 eflags.push_back(op6);
13852 eflags.push_back(op5);
13853 eflags.push_back(op4);
13854 eflags.push_back(this->astCtxt->bvfalse()); /* Reserved */
13855 eflags.push_back(op3);
13856 eflags.push_back(this->astCtxt->bvfalse()); /* Reserved */
13857 eflags.push_back(op2);
13858 eflags.push_back(this->astCtxt->bvtrue()); /* Reserved */
13859 eflags.push_back(op1);
13860
13861 auto node = this->astCtxt->zx(
13862 dst.getBitSize() - static_cast<triton::uint32>(eflags.size()),
13863 this->astCtxt->concat(eflags)
13864 );
13865
13866 /* Create symbolic expression */
13867 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, dst, "PUSHFD operation");
13868
13869 /* Spread taint */
13870 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintAssignment(dst, src1);
13871 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src2);
13872 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src3);
13873 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src4);
13874 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src5);
13875 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src6);
13876 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src7);
13877 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src8);
13878 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src9);
13879 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src10);
13880 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src11);
13881 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src12);
13882 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src13);
13883 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src14);
13884
13885 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
13886 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
13887 }

13892
13893 /* Create the semantics - side effect */

13896 auto src1 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_CF));
13897 auto src2 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_PF));
13898 auto src3 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_AF));
13899 auto src4 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_ZF));
13900 auto src5 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_SF));
13901 auto src6 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_TF));
13902 auto src7 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_IF));
13903 auto src8 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_DF));
13904 auto src9 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_OF));
13905 auto src10 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_NT));
13906 auto src11 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_AC));
13907 auto src12 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_VIF));
13908 auto src13 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_VIP));
13909 auto src14 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_ID));
13910
13911 /* Create symbolic operands */
13912 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src1);
13913 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src2);
13914 auto op3 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src3);
13915 auto op4 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src4);
13916 auto op5 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src5);
13917 auto op6 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src6);
13918 auto op7 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src7);
13919 auto op8 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src8);

13922 auto op11 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src11);
13923 auto op12 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src12);

13956 this->astCtxt->concat(eflags)
13957 );

13966 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src4);
13967 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src5);
13968 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src6);
13969 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src7);
13970 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src8);
13971 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src9);
13972 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src10);
13973 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src11);
13974 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src12);
13975 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src13);
13976 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src14);

13978 /* Update the symbolic control flow */

13982
13983 void x86Semantics::pxor_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
13984 auto& dst = inst.operands[0];
13985 auto& src = inst.operands[1];
13986
13987 /* Create symbolic operands */
13988 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, dst);
13989 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src);
13990
13991 /* Create the semantics */
13992 auto node = this->astCtxt->bvxor(op1, op2);
13993
13994 /* Create symbolic expression */
13995 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, dst, "PXOR operation");
13996
13997 /* Update the x87 FPU Tag Word */
13998 this->updateFTW(inst, expr);
13999
14000 /* Spread taint */
14001 if (dst.getType() == OP_REG && src.getRegister() == dst.getRegister())
14002 this->taintEngine->setTaint(src, false);
14003 else
14004 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src);
14005
14006 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
14007 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
14008 }
14009
14010
14011 void x86Semantics::rcl_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
14012 auto& dst = inst.operands[0];
14013 auto& src = inst.operands[1];
14014 auto srcCf = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_CF));
14015
14016 /* Create symbolic operands */
14017 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, dst);
14018 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src);
14019 auto op2bis = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(src);
14020 auto op3 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, srcCf);
14021
14022 switch (dst.getBitSize()) {
14023 /* Mask: 0x1f without MOD */
14024 case triton::bitsize::qword:
14025 op2 = this->astCtxt->bvand(
14026 op2,
14027 this->astCtxt->bv(triton::bitsize::qword-1, src.getBitSize())
14028 );
14029 break;
14030
14031 /* Mask: 0x1f without MOD */
14032 case triton::bitsize::dword:
14033 op2 = this->astCtxt->bvand(
14034 op2,
14035 this->astCtxt->bv(triton::bitsize::dword-1, src.getBitSize())
14036 );
14037 break;
14038
14039 /* Mask: 0x1f MOD size + 1 */
14040 case triton::bitsize::word:
14041 case triton::bitsize::byte:
14042 op2 = this->astCtxt->bvsmod(
14043 this->astCtxt->bvand(
14044 op2,
14045 this->astCtxt->bv(triton::bitsize::dword-1, src.getBitSize())),
14046 this->astCtxt->bv(dst.getBitSize()+1, src.getBitSize())
14047 );
14048 break;
14049
14050 default:
14051 throw triton::exceptions::Semantics("x86Semantics::rcl_s(): Invalid destination size");
14052 }
14053
14054 /* Create the semantics */
14055 auto node1 = this->astCtxt->bvrol(
14056 this->astCtxt->concat(op3, op1),
14057 this->astCtxt->zx(((op1->getBitvectorSize() + op3->getBitvectorSize()) - op2->getBitvectorSize()), op2)
14058 );
14059
14060 /* Create symbolic expression */
14061 auto expr1 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicVolatileExpression(inst, node1, "RCL tempory operation");
14062
14063 /* Spread taint */
14064 expr1->isTainted = this->taintEngine->isTainted(dst) | this->taintEngine->isTainted(src);
14065
14066 /* Create the semantics */
14067 auto node2 = this->astCtxt->extract(dst.getBitSize()-1, 0, node1);
14068
14069 /* Create symbolic expression */
14070 auto expr2 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node2, dst, "RCL operation");
14071
14072 /* Spread taint */
14073 expr2->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src);
14074 expr2->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, srcCf);
14075
14076 /* Update symbolic flags */
14077 this->cfRcl_s(inst, expr2, node1, op2bis);
14078 this->ofRol_s(inst, expr2, dst, op2bis); /* Same as ROL */
14079
14080 /* Tag undefined flags */
14081 if (op2->evaluate() > 1) {
14082 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_OF));
14083 }
14084
14085 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
14086 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
14087 }
14088
14089
14090 void x86Semantics::rcr_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
14091 auto& dst = inst.operands[0];
14092 auto& src = inst.operands[1];
14093 auto srcCf = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_CF));
14094
14095 /* Create symbolic operands */
14096 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, dst);
14097 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src);
14098 auto op3 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, srcCf);
14099
14100 switch (dst.getBitSize()) {
14101 /* Mask: 0x3f without MOD */
14102 case triton::bitsize::qword:
14103 op2 = this->astCtxt->bvand(
14104 op2,
14105 this->astCtxt->bv(triton::bitsize::qword-1, src.getBitSize())
14106 );
14107 break;
14108
14109 /* Mask: 0x1f without MOD */
14110 case triton::bitsize::dword:
14111 op2 = this->astCtxt->bvand(
14112 op2,
14113 this->astCtxt->bv(triton::bitsize::dword-1, src.getBitSize())
14114 );
14115 break;
14116
14117 /* Mask: 0x1f MOD size + 1 */
14118 case triton::bitsize::word:
14119 case triton::bitsize::byte:
14120 op2 = this->astCtxt->bvsmod(
14121 this->astCtxt->bvand(
14122 op2,
14123 this->astCtxt->bv(triton::bitsize::dword-1, src.getBitSize())),
14124 this->astCtxt->bv(dst.getBitSize()+1, src.getBitSize())
14125 );
14126 break;
14127
14128 default:
14129 throw triton::exceptions::Semantics("x86Semantics::rcr_s(): Invalid destination size");
14130 }
14131
14132 /* Create the semantics */
14133 auto node1 = this->astCtxt->bvror(
14134 this->astCtxt->concat(op3, op1),
14135 this->astCtxt->zx(((op1->getBitvectorSize() + op3->getBitvectorSize()) - op2->getBitvectorSize()), op2)
14136 );
14137
14138 /* Create symbolic expression */
14139 auto expr1 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicVolatileExpression(inst, node1, "RCR tempory operation");
14140
14141 /* Spread taint */
14142 expr1->isTainted = this->taintEngine->isTainted(dst) | this->taintEngine->isTainted(src);
14143
14144 /* Create the semantics */
14145 auto node2 = this->astCtxt->extract(dst.getBitSize()-1, 0, node1);
14146
14147 /* Create symbolic expression */
14148 auto expr2 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node2, dst, "RCR operation");
14149
14150 /* Spread taint */
14151 expr2->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src);
14152 expr2->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, srcCf);
14153
14154 /* Update symbolic flags */
14155 this->ofRcr_s(inst, expr2, dst, op1, op2); /* OF must be set before CF */
14156 this->cfRcr_s(inst, expr2, dst, node1, op2);
14157
14158 /* Tag undefined flags */
14159 if (op2->evaluate() > 1) {
14160 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_OF));
14161 }
14162
14163 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
14164 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
14165 }
14166
14167
14168 void x86Semantics::rdtsc_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
14169 auto dst1 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_EDX));
14170 auto dst2 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_EAX));
14171
14172 /* Create symbolic operands */
14173 auto op1 = this->astCtxt->bv(0, dst1.getBitSize());
14174 auto op2 = this->astCtxt->bv(this->symbolicEngine->getSymbolicExpressions().size(), dst2.getBitSize());
14175
14176 /* Create symbolic expression */
14177 auto expr1 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, op1, dst1, "RDTSC EDX operation");
14178 auto expr2 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, op2, dst2, "RDTSC EAX operation");
14179
14180 /* Spread taint */
14181 expr1->isTainted = this->taintEngine->setTaint(dst1, triton::engines::taint::UNTAINTED);
14182 expr2->isTainted = this->taintEngine->setTaint(dst2, triton::engines::taint::UNTAINTED);
14183
14184 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
14185 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
14186 }
14187
14188
14189 void x86Semantics::ret_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
14190 auto stack = this->architecture->getStackPointer();
14191 auto stackValue = static_cast<triton::uint64>(this->architecture->getConcreteRegisterValue(stack));
14192 auto pc = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getProgramCounter());
14193 auto sp = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(triton::arch::MemoryAccess(stackValue, stack.getSize()));
14194
14195 /* Create symbolic operands */
14196 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, sp);
14197
14198 /* Create the semantics */
14199 auto node = op1;
14200
14201 /* Create symbolic expression */
14202 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, pc, "Program Counter");
14203
14204 /* Spread taint */
14205 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintAssignment(pc, sp);
14206
14207 /* Create the semantics - side effect */
14208 alignAddStack_s(inst, sp.getSize());
14209
14210 /* Create the semantics - side effect */
14211 if (inst.operands.size() > 0) {
14212 auto offset = inst.operands[0].getImmediate();
14213 this->symbolicEngine->getImmediateAst(inst, offset);
14214 alignAddStack_s(inst, static_cast<triton::uint32>(offset.getValue()));
14215 }
14216
14217 /* Create the path constraint */
14218 this->symbolicEngine->pushPathConstraint(inst, expr);
14219 }
14220
14221
14222 void x86Semantics::rol_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
14223 auto& dst = inst.operands[0];
14224 auto& src = inst.operands[1];
14225
14226 /* Create symbolic operands */
14227 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, dst);
14228 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src);
14229 auto op2bis = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(src);
14230
14231 switch (dst.getBitSize()) {
14232 /* Mask 0x3f MOD size */
14233 case triton::bitsize::qword:
14234 op2 = this->astCtxt->bvsmod(
14235 this->astCtxt->bvand(
14236 op2,
14237 this->astCtxt->bv(triton::bitsize::qword-1, src.getBitSize())),
14238 this->astCtxt->bv(dst.getBitSize(), src.getBitSize())
14239 );
14240
14241 op2bis = this->astCtxt->bvand(
14242 op2bis,
14243 this->astCtxt->bv(triton::bitsize::qword-1, src.getBitSize())
14244 );
14245 break;
14246
14247 /* Mask 0x1f MOD size */
14248 case triton::bitsize::dword:
14249 case triton::bitsize::word:
14250 case triton::bitsize::byte:
14251 op2 = this->astCtxt->bvsmod(
14252 this->astCtxt->bvand(
14253 op2,
14254 this->astCtxt->bv(triton::bitsize::dword-1, src.getBitSize())),
14255 this->astCtxt->bv(dst.getBitSize(), src.getBitSize())
14256 );
14257
14258 op2bis = this->astCtxt->bvand(
14259 op2bis,
14260 this->astCtxt->bv(triton::bitsize::dword-1, src.getBitSize())
14261 );
14262 break;
14263
14264 default:
14265 throw triton::exceptions::Semantics("x86Semantics::rol_s(): Invalid destination size");
14266 }
14267
14268 /* Create the semantics */
14269 auto node = this->astCtxt->bvrol(
14270 op1,
14271 this->astCtxt->zx(op1->getBitvectorSize() - op2->getBitvectorSize(), op2)
14272 );
14273
14274 /* Create symbolic expression */
14275 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, dst, "ROL operation");
14276
14277 /* Spread taint */
14278 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src);
14279
14280 /* Update symbolic flags */
14281 this->cfRol_s(inst, expr, dst, op2bis);
14282 this->ofRol_s(inst, expr, dst, op2bis);
14283
14284 /* Tag undefined flags */
14285 if (op2->evaluate() > 1) {
14286 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_OF));
14287 }
14288
14289 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
14290 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
14291 }
14292

14294 void x86Semantics::ror_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
14295 auto& dst = inst.operands[0];
14296 auto& src = inst.operands[1];
14297
14298 /* Create symbolic operands */
14299 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, dst);
14300 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src);
14301 auto op2bis = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(src);
14302
14303 switch (dst.getBitSize()) {
14304 /* Mask 0x3f MOD size */
14305 case triton::bitsize::qword:
14306 op2 = this->astCtxt->bvsmod(
14307 this->astCtxt->bvand(
14308 op2,
14309 this->astCtxt->bv(triton::bitsize::qword-1, src.getBitSize())),
14310 this->astCtxt->bv(dst.getBitSize(), src.getBitSize())
14311 );
14312

14314 op2bis,
14315 this->astCtxt->bv(triton::bitsize::qword-1, src.getBitSize())
14316 );
14317 break;
14318
14319 /* Mask 0x1f MOD size */
14320 case triton::bitsize::dword:
14321 case triton::bitsize::word:
14322 case triton::bitsize::byte:
14323 op2 = this->astCtxt->bvsmod(
14324 this->astCtxt->bvand(
14325 op2,
14326 this->astCtxt->bv(triton::bitsize::dword-1, src.getBitSize())),
14327 this->astCtxt->bv(dst.getBitSize(), src.getBitSize())
14328 );
14329
14330 op2bis = this->astCtxt->bvand(
14331 op2bis,
14332 this->astCtxt->bv(triton::bitsize::dword-1, src.getBitSize())
14333 );
14334 break;
14335
14336 default:
14337 throw triton::exceptions::Semantics("x86Semantics::ror_s(): Invalid destination size");
14338 }
14339
14340 /* Create the semantics */
14341 auto node = this->astCtxt->bvror(
14342 op1,
14343 this->astCtxt->zx(op1->getBitvectorSize() - op2->getBitvectorSize(), op2)

14353 this->cfRor_s(inst, expr, dst, op2);
14354 this->ofRor_s(inst, expr, dst, op2bis);
14355
14356 /* Tag undefined flags */
14357 if (op2->evaluate() > 1) {
14358 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_OF));
14359 }
14360
14361 /* Update the symbolic control flow */

14365
14366 void x86Semantics::rorx_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
14367 auto& dst = inst.operands[0];
14368 auto& src1 = inst.operands[1];
14369 auto& src2 = inst.operands[2];
14370
14371 /* Create symbolic operands */
14372 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src1);
14373 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src2);
14374
14375 switch (dst.getBitSize()) {
14376 /* Mask 0x3f MOD size */
14377 case triton::bitsize::qword:
14378 op2 = this->astCtxt->bvand(op2, this->astCtxt->bv(triton::bitsize::qword-1, src2.getBitSize()));
14379 break;
14380
14381 /* Mask 0x1f MOD size */
14382 case triton::bitsize::dword:
14383 op2 = this->astCtxt->bvand(op2, this->astCtxt->bv(triton::bitsize::dword-1, src2.getBitSize()));
14384 break;
14385
14386 default:
14387 throw triton::exceptions::Semantics("x86Semantics::rorx_s(): Invalid destination size");
14388 }
14389
14390 /* Create the semantics */
14391 auto node = this->astCtxt->bvror(
14392 op1,
14393 this->astCtxt->zx(op1->getBitvectorSize() - op2->getBitvectorSize(), op2)
14394 );
14395
14396 /* Create symbolic expression */
14397 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, dst, "RORX operation");
14398
14399 /* Spread taint */
14400 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintAssignment(dst, src1);
14401 expr->isTainted |= this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src2);
14402
14403 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
14404 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
14405 }

14407
14408 void x86Semantics::sahf_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
14409 auto dst1 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_SF));
14410 auto dst2 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_ZF));
14411 auto dst3 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_AF));
14412 auto dst4 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_PF));
14413 auto dst5 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_CF));
14414 auto src = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_AH));
14415
14416 /* Create symbolic operands */
14417 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src);
14418
14419 /* Create the semantics */
14420 auto node1 = this->astCtxt->extract(7, 7, op1);
14421 auto node2 = this->astCtxt->extract(6, 6, op1);
14422 auto node3 = this->astCtxt->extract(4, 4, op1);
14423 auto node4 = this->astCtxt->extract(2, 2, op1);
14424 auto node5 = this->astCtxt->extract(0, 0, op1);
14425
14426 /* Create symbolic expression */
14427 auto expr1 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node1, dst1.getRegister(), "SAHF SF operation");
14428 auto expr2 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node2, dst2.getRegister(), "SAHF ZF operation");
14429 auto expr3 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node3, dst3.getRegister(), "SAHF AF operation");
14430 auto expr4 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node4, dst4.getRegister(), "SAHF PF operation");
14431 auto expr5 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node5, dst5.getRegister(), "SAHF CF operation");
14432
14433 /* Spread taint */
14434 expr1->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintAssignment(dst1, src);
14435 expr2->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintAssignment(dst2, src);
14436 expr3->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintAssignment(dst3, src);
14437 expr4->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintAssignment(dst4, src);
14438 expr5->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintAssignment(dst5, src);
14439
14440 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
14441 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
14442 }
14443
14444
14445 void x86Semantics::sar_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
14446 auto& dst = inst.operands[0];
14447 auto& src = inst.operands[1];
14448
14449 /* Create symbolic operands */
14450 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, dst);
14451 auto op2 = this->astCtxt->zx(dst.getBitSize() - src.getBitSize(), this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src));
14452
14453 if (dst.getBitSize() == triton::bitsize::qword)
14454 op2 = this->astCtxt->bvand(op2, this->astCtxt->bv(triton::bitsize::qword-1, dst.getBitSize()));
14455 else
14456 op2 = this->astCtxt->bvand(op2, this->astCtxt->bv(triton::bitsize::dword-1, dst.getBitSize()));
14457
14458 /* Create the semantics */
14459 auto node = this->astCtxt->bvashr(op1, op2);
14460
14461 /* Create symbolic expression */
14462 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, dst, "SAR operation");
14463
14464 /* Spread taint */
14465 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src);
14466
14467 /* Update symbolic flags */
14468 this->cfSar_s(inst, expr, dst, op1, op2);
14469 this->ofSar_s(inst, expr, dst, op2);
14470 this->pfShl_s(inst, expr, dst, op2); /* Same that shl */
14471 this->sfShl_s(inst, expr, dst, op2); /* Same that shl */
14472 this->zfShl_s(inst, expr, dst, op2); /* Same that shl */
14473
14474 /* Tag undefined flags */
14475 if (op2->evaluate() != 0) {
14476 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_AF));
14477 }
14478
14479 if (op2->evaluate() > 1) {
14480 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_OF));
14481 }
14482
14483 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
14484 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
14485 }

14488 void x86Semantics::sarx_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
14489 auto& dst = inst.operands[0];
14490 auto& src1 = inst.operands[1];
14491 auto& src2 = inst.operands[2];
14492

14498 /* Mask 0x3f MOD size */

14500 op2 = this->astCtxt->bvand(op2, this->astCtxt->bv(triton::bitsize::qword-1, src2.getBitSize()));
14501 break;
14502
14503 /* Mask 0x1f MOD size */
14504 case triton::bitsize::dword:
14505 op2 = this->astCtxt->bvand(op2, this->astCtxt->bv(triton::bitsize::dword-1, src2.getBitSize()));
14506 break;
14507

14526
14527 void x86Semantics::sbb_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
14528 auto& dst = inst.operands[0];
14529 auto& src = inst.operands[1];
14530 auto srcCf = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_CF));
14531
14532 /* Create symbolic operands */
14533 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, dst);
14534 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src);
14535 auto op3 = this->astCtxt->zx(src.getBitSize()-1, this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, srcCf));
14536
14537 /* Create the semantics */
14538 auto node = this->astCtxt->bvsub(op1, this->astCtxt->bvadd(op2, op3));
14539
14540 /* Create symbolic expression */
14541 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, dst, "SBB operation");
14542
14543 /* Spread taint */
14544 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src);
14545 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, srcCf);
14546
14547 /* Update symbolic flags */
14548 this->af_s(inst, expr, dst, op1, op2);
14549 this->cfSub_s(inst, expr, dst, op1, op2);
14550 this->ofSub_s(inst, expr, dst, op1, op2);
14551 this->pf_s(inst, expr, dst);
14552 this->sf_s(inst, expr, dst);
14553 this->zf_s(inst, expr, dst);
14554
14555 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
14556 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
14557 }
14558
14559
14560 void x86Semantics::scasb_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
14561 auto& dst = inst.operands[0];
14562 auto& src = inst.operands[1];
14563 auto index = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getParentRegister(ID_REG_X86_DI));
14564 auto cx = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getParentRegister(ID_REG_X86_CX));
14565 auto df = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_DF));
14566
14567 /* If the REP prefix is defined, convert REP into REPE */
14568 if (inst.getPrefix() == triton::arch::x86::ID_PREFIX_REP)
14569 inst.setPrefix(triton::arch::x86::ID_PREFIX_REPE);
14570
14571 /* Check if there is a REP prefix and a counter to zero */
14572 if (inst.getPrefix() != triton::arch::x86::ID_PREFIX_INVALID && this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(cx)->evaluate().is_zero()) {
14573 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
14574 return;
14575 }
14576
14577 /* Create symbolic operands */
14578 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, dst);
14579 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src);
14580 auto op3 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, index);
14581 auto op4 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, df);
14582
14583 /* Create the semantics */
14584 auto node1 = this->astCtxt->bvsub(op1, op2);
14585 auto node2 = this->astCtxt->ite(
14586 this->astCtxt->equal(op4, this->astCtxt->bvfalse()),
14587 this->astCtxt->bvadd(op3, this->astCtxt->bv(triton::size::byte, index.getBitSize())),
14588 this->astCtxt->bvsub(op3, this->astCtxt->bv(triton::size::byte, index.getBitSize()))
14589 );
14590
14591 /* Create symbolic expression */
14592 auto expr1 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicVolatileExpression(inst, node1, "SCASB operation");
14593 auto expr2 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node2, index, "Index operation");
14594
14595 /* Spread taint */
14596 expr1->isTainted = this->taintEngine->isTainted(dst) | this->taintEngine->isTainted(src);
14597 expr2->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(index, index);
14598
14599 /* Update symbolic flags */
14600 this->af_s(inst, expr1, dst, op1, op2, true);
14601 this->cfSub_s(inst, expr1, dst, op1, op2, true);
14602 this->ofSub_s(inst, expr1, dst, op1, op2, true);
14603 this->pf_s(inst, expr1, dst, true);
14604 this->sf_s(inst, expr1, dst, true);
14605 this->zf_s(inst, expr1, dst, true);
14606
14607 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
14608 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
14609 }
14610

14716 void x86Semantics::scasw_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {

14718 auto& src = inst.operands[1];
14719 auto index = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getParentRegister(ID_REG_X86_DI));
14720 auto cx = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getParentRegister(ID_REG_X86_CX));
14721 auto df = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_DF));
14722
14723 /* If the REP prefix is defined, convert REP into REPE */
14724 if (inst.getPrefix() == triton::arch::x86::ID_PREFIX_REP)
14725 inst.setPrefix(triton::arch::x86::ID_PREFIX_REPE);
14726
14727 /* Check if there is a REP prefix and a counter to zero */
14728 if (inst.getPrefix() != triton::arch::x86::ID_PREFIX_INVALID && this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(cx)->evaluate().is_zero()) {
14729 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
14730 return;
14731 }
14732
14733 /* Create symbolic operands */
14734 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, dst);
14735 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src);
14736 auto op3 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, index);
14737 auto op4 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, df);
14738
14739 /* Create the semantics */
14740 auto node1 = this->astCtxt->bvsub(op1, op2);
14741 auto node2 = this->astCtxt->ite(
14742 this->astCtxt->equal(op4, this->astCtxt->bvfalse()),
14743 this->astCtxt->bvadd(op3, this->astCtxt->bv(triton::size::word, index.getBitSize())),
14744 this->astCtxt->bvsub(op3, this->astCtxt->bv(triton::size::word, index.getBitSize()))
14745 );
14746
14747 /* Create symbolic expression */
14748 auto expr1 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicVolatileExpression(inst, node1, "SCASW operation");
14749 auto expr2 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node2, index, "Index operation");
14750
14751 /* Spread taint */
14752 expr1->isTainted = this->taintEngine->isTainted(dst) | this->taintEngine->isTainted(src);
14753 expr2->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(index, index);
14754
14755 /* Update symbolic flags */
14756 this->af_s(inst, expr1, dst, op1, op2, true);
14757 this->cfSub_s(inst, expr1, dst, op1, op2, true);
14758 this->ofSub_s(inst, expr1, dst, op1, op2, true);
14759 this->pf_s(inst, expr1, dst, true);
14760 this->sf_s(inst, expr1, dst, true);
14761 this->zf_s(inst, expr1, dst, true);
14762
14763 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
14764 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
14765 }
14766
14767
14768 void x86Semantics::seta_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
14769 auto& dst = inst.operands[0];
14770 auto cf = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_CF));
14771 auto zf = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_ZF));
14772
14773 /* Create symbolic operands */
14774 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, cf);
14775 auto op3 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, zf);
14776
14777 /* Create the semantics */
14778 auto node = this->astCtxt->ite(
14779 this->astCtxt->equal(
14780 this->astCtxt->bvand(
14781 this->astCtxt->bvnot(op2),
14782 this->astCtxt->bvnot(op3)
14783 ),
14784 this->astCtxt->bvtrue()
14785 ),
14786 this->astCtxt->bv(1, dst.getBitSize()),
14787 this->astCtxt->bv(0, dst.getBitSize())
14788 );
14789
14790 /* Create symbolic expression */
14791 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, dst, "SETA operation");
14792
14793 /* Set condition flag */
14794 if (op2->evaluate().is_zero() && op3->evaluate().is_zero()) {
14795 inst.setConditionTaken(true);
14796 }
14797
14798 /* Spread taint */
14799 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintAssignment(dst, cf);
14800 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, zf);
14801
14802 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
14803 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
14804 }

15282
15283
15284 void x86Semantics::shl_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
15285 auto& dst = inst.operands[0];
15286 auto& src = inst.operands[1];
15287
15288 /* Create symbolic operands */
15289 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, dst);
15290 auto op2 = this->astCtxt->zx(dst.getBitSize() - src.getBitSize(), this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src));
15291 auto op2bis = op2;
15292
15293 if (dst.getBitSize() == triton::bitsize::qword)
15294 op2 = this->astCtxt->bvand(op2, this->astCtxt->bv(triton::bitsize::qword-1, dst.getBitSize()));
15295 else
15296 op2 = this->astCtxt->bvand(op2, this->astCtxt->bv(triton::bitsize::dword-1, dst.getBitSize()));
15297
15298 /* Create the semantics */
15299 auto node = this->astCtxt->bvshl(op1, op2);
15300
15301 /* Create symbolic expression */
15302 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, dst, "SHL operation");
15303
15304 /* Spread taint */
15305 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src);
15306
15307 /* Update symbolic flags */
15308 this->cfShl_s(inst, expr, dst, op1, op2);
15309 this->ofShl_s(inst, expr, dst, op1, op2);
15310 this->pfShl_s(inst, expr, dst, op2);
15311 this->sfShl_s(inst, expr, dst, op2);
15312 this->zfShl_s(inst, expr, dst, op2);
15313
15314 /* Tag undefined flags */
15315 if (op2->evaluate() != 0) {
15316 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_AF));
15317 }
15318
15319 if (op2bis->evaluate() > dst.getBitSize()) {
15320 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_CF));
15321 }
15322
15323 if (op2->evaluate() > 1) {
15324 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_OF));
15325 }
15326
15327 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
15328 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
15329 }
15330
15331
15332 void x86Semantics::shld_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
15333 auto& dst = inst.operands[0];
15334 auto& src1 = inst.operands[1];
15335 auto& src2 = inst.operands[2];
15336
15337 /* Create symbolic operands */
15338 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, dst);
15339 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src1);
15340 auto op3 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src2);
15341 auto op3bis = op3;
15342
15343 switch (dst.getBitSize()) {
15344 /* Mask 0x3f MOD size */
15345 case triton::bitsize::qword:
15346 op3 = this->astCtxt->bvsmod(
15347 this->astCtxt->bvand(
15348 op3,
15349 this->astCtxt->bv(triton::bitsize::qword-1, src2.getBitSize())),
15350 this->astCtxt->bv(dst.getBitSize(), src2.getBitSize())
15351 );
15352 break;
15353
15354 /* Mask 0x1f MOD size */
15355 case triton::bitsize::dword:
15356 case triton::bitsize::word:
15357 op3 = this->astCtxt->bvsmod(
15358 this->astCtxt->bvand(
15359 op3,
15360 this->astCtxt->bv(triton::bitsize::dword-1, src2.getBitSize())),
15361 this->astCtxt->bv(triton::bitsize::dword, src2.getBitSize())
15362 );
15363 break;
15364
15365 default:
15366 throw triton::exceptions::Semantics("x86Semantics::shld_s(): Invalid destination size");
15367 }
15368
15369 /* Create the semantics */
15370 auto node = this->astCtxt->extract(
15371 dst.getBitSize()-1, 0,
15372 this->astCtxt->bvrol(
15373 this->astCtxt->concat(op2, op1),
15374 this->astCtxt->zx(((op1->getBitvectorSize() + op2->getBitvectorSize()) - op3->getBitvectorSize()), op3)
15375 )
15376 );
15377
15378 /* Create symbolic expression */
15379 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, dst, "SHLD operation");
15380
15381 /* Spread taint */
15382 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintAssignment(dst, src1);
15383 expr->isTainted |= this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src2);
15384
15385 /* Update symbolic flags */
15386 this->cfShld_s(inst, expr, dst, op1, op2, op3);
15387 this->ofShld_s(inst, expr, dst, op1, op2, op3);
15388 this->pfShl_s(inst, expr, dst, op3); /* Same that shl */
15389 this->sfShld_s(inst, expr, dst, op1, op2, op3);
15390 this->zfShl_s(inst, expr, dst, op3); /* Same that shl */
15391
15392 /* Tag undefined flags */
15393 if (op3->evaluate() != 0) {
15394 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_AF));
15395 }
15396
15397 if (op3->evaluate() > 1) {
15398 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_OF));
15399 }
15400
15401 if (op3bis->evaluate() > dst.getBitSize()) {
15402 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_AF));
15403 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_CF));
15404 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_OF));
15405 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_PF));
15406 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_SF));
15407 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_ZF));
15408 if (dst.getType() == triton::arch::OP_REG)
15409 this->undefined_s(inst, dst.getRegister());
15410 }
15411
15412 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
15413 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
15414 }
15415
15416
15417 void x86Semantics::shlx_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
15418 auto& dst = inst.operands[0];
15419 auto& src1 = inst.operands[1];
15420 auto& src2 = inst.operands[2];
15421
15422 /* Create symbolic operands */
15423 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src1);
15424 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src2);
15425
15426 switch (dst.getBitSize()) {
15427 /* Mask 0x3f MOD size */
15428 case triton::bitsize::qword:
15429 op2 = this->astCtxt->bvand(op2, this->astCtxt->bv(triton::bitsize::qword-1, src2.getBitSize()));
15430 break;
15431
15432 /* Mask 0x1f MOD size */
15433 case triton::bitsize::dword:
15434 op2 = this->astCtxt->bvand(op2, this->astCtxt->bv(triton::bitsize::dword-1, src2.getBitSize()));
15435 break;
15436
15437 default:
15438 throw triton::exceptions::Semantics("x86Semantics::shlx_s(): Invalid destination size");
15439 }
15440
15441 /* Create the semantics */
15442 auto node = this->astCtxt->bvshl(op1, op2);
15443
15444 /* Create symbolic expression */
15445 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, dst, "SHLX operation");
15446
15447 /* Spread taint */
15448 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintAssignment(dst, src1);
15449 expr->isTainted |= this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src2);
15450
15451 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
15452 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
15453 }
15454
15455
15456 void x86Semantics::shr_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
15457 auto& dst = inst.operands[0];
15458 auto& src = inst.operands[1];
15459
15460 /* Create symbolic operands */
15461 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, dst);
15462 auto op2 = this->astCtxt->zx(dst.getBitSize() - src.getBitSize(), this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src));
15463 auto op2bis = op2;
15464
15465 if (dst.getBitSize() == triton::bitsize::qword)
15466 op2 = this->astCtxt->bvand(op2, this->astCtxt->bv(triton::bitsize::qword-1, dst.getBitSize()));
15467 else
15468 op2 = this->astCtxt->bvand(op2, this->astCtxt->bv(triton::bitsize::dword-1, dst.getBitSize()));
15469
15470 /* Create the semantics */
15471 auto node = this->astCtxt->bvlshr(op1, op2);
15472
15473 /* Create symbolic expression */
15474 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, dst, "SHR operation");
15475
15476 /* Spread taint */
15477 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src);
15478
15479 /* Update symbolic flags */
15480 this->cfShr_s(inst, expr, dst, op1, op2);
15481 this->ofShr_s(inst, expr, dst, op1, op2);
15482 this->pfShl_s(inst, expr, dst, op2); /* Same that shl */
15483 this->sfShl_s(inst, expr, dst, op2); /* Same that shl */
15484 this->zfShl_s(inst, expr, dst, op2); /* Same that shl */
15485
15486 /* Tag undefined flags */
15487 if (op2->evaluate() != 0) {
15488 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_AF));
15489 }
15490
15491 if (op2bis->evaluate() > dst.getBitSize()) {
15492 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_CF));
15493 }
15494
15495 if (op2->evaluate() > 1) {
15496 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_OF));
15497 }
15498
15499 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
15500 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
15501 }

15669
15670 void x86Semantics::stosb_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
15671 auto& dst = inst.operands[0];
15672 auto& src = inst.operands[1];
15673 auto index = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getParentRegister(ID_REG_X86_DI));
15674 auto cx = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getParentRegister(ID_REG_X86_CX));
15675 auto df = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_DF));
15676
15677 /* Check if there is a REP prefix and a counter to zero */
15678 if (inst.getPrefix() != triton::arch::x86::ID_PREFIX_INVALID && this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(cx)->evaluate().is_zero()) {
15679 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
15680 return;
15681 }
15682
15683 /* Create symbolic operands */
15684 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src);
15685 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, index);
15686 auto op3 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, df);
15687
15688 /* Create the semantics */
15689 auto node1 = op1;
15690 auto node2 = this->astCtxt->ite(
15691 this->astCtxt->equal(op3, this->astCtxt->bvfalse()),
15692 this->astCtxt->bvadd(op2, this->astCtxt->bv(triton::size::byte, index.getBitSize())),
15693 this->astCtxt->bvsub(op2, this->astCtxt->bv(triton::size::byte, index.getBitSize()))
15694 );
15695
15696 /* Create symbolic expression */
15697 auto expr1 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node1, dst, "STOSB operation");
15698 auto expr2 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node2, index, "Index operation");
15699
15700 /* Spread taint */
15701 expr1->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintAssignment(dst, src);
15702 expr2->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(index, index);
15703
15704 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
15705 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
15706 }

15855
15856 void x86Semantics::syscall_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
15857 auto dst1 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getParentRegister(ID_REG_X86_CX));
15858 auto src1 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getProgramCounter());
15859
15860 /* Create symbolic operands */
15861 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src1);
15862
15863 /* Create the semantics */
15864 auto node1 = this->astCtxt->bvadd(op1, this->astCtxt->bv(inst.getSize(), src1.getBitSize()));
15865
15866 /* Create symbolic expression */
15867 auto expr1 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node1, dst1, "SYSCALL RCX operation");
15868
15869 /* Spread taint */
15870 expr1->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintAssignment(dst1, src1);
15871
15872 /* 64-bit */
15873 if (src1.getBitSize() == 64) {
15874 auto dst2 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_R11));
15875 auto src2 = triton::arch::OperandWrapper(this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_EFLAGS));
15876 /* Create symbolic operands */
15877 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src2);
15878 /* Create symbolic expression */
15879 auto expr2 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, op2, dst2, "SYSCALL R11 operation");
15880 /* Spread taint */
15881 expr2->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintAssignment(dst2, src2);
15882 }
15883
15884 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
15885 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
15886 }
15887
15888
15889 void x86Semantics::sysenter_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
15890 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
15891 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
15892 }
15893
15894
15895 void x86Semantics::test_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
15896 auto& src1 = inst.operands[0];
15897 auto& src2 = inst.operands[1];
15898
15899 /* Create symbolic operands */
15900 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src1);
15901 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src2);
15902
15903 /* Create the semantics */
15904 auto node = this->astCtxt->bvand(op1, op2);
15905
15906 /* Create symbolic expression */
15907 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicVolatileExpression(inst, node, "TEST operation");
15908
15909 /* Spread taint */
15910 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->isTainted(src1) | this->taintEngine->isTainted(src2);
15911
15912 /* Update symbolic flags */
15913 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_AF));
15914 this->clearFlag_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_CF), "Clears carry flag");
15915 this->clearFlag_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_OF), "Clears overflow flag");
15916 this->pf_s(inst, expr, src1, true);
15917 this->sf_s(inst, expr, src1, true);
15918 this->zf_s(inst, expr, src1, true);
15919
15920 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
15921 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
15922 }

15925 void x86Semantics::tzcnt_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {

15927 auto& src = inst.operands[1];
15928 auto bvSize1 = dst.getBitSize();
15929 auto bvSize2 = src.getBitSize();
15930
15931 /* Create symbolic operands */
15932 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src);
15933
15934 /* Create the semantics */
15935 triton::ast::SharedAbstractNode node = nullptr;
15936 switch (src.getSize()) {
15937 case triton::size::byte:
15938 node = this->astCtxt->ite(
15939 this->astCtxt->equal(op1, this->astCtxt->bv(0, bvSize2)),
15940 this->astCtxt->bv(bvSize1, bvSize1),
15941 this->astCtxt->ite(this->astCtxt->equal(this->astCtxt->extract(0, 0, op1), this->astCtxt->bvtrue()), this->astCtxt->bv(0, bvSize1),
15942 this->astCtxt->ite(this->astCtxt->equal(this->astCtxt->extract(1, 1, op1), this->astCtxt->bvtrue()), this->astCtxt->bv(1, bvSize1),
15943 this->astCtxt->ite(this->astCtxt->equal(this->astCtxt->extract(2, 2, op1), this->astCtxt->bvtrue()), this->astCtxt->bv(2, bvSize1),
15944 this->astCtxt->ite(this->astCtxt->equal(this->astCtxt->extract(3, 3, op1), this->astCtxt->bvtrue()), this->astCtxt->bv(3, bvSize1),
15945 this->astCtxt->ite(this->astCtxt->equal(this->astCtxt->extract(4, 4, op1), this->astCtxt->bvtrue()), this->astCtxt->bv(4, bvSize1),
15946 this->astCtxt->ite(this->astCtxt->equal(this->astCtxt->extract(5, 5, op1), this->astCtxt->bvtrue()), this->astCtxt->bv(5, bvSize1),
15947 this->astCtxt->ite(this->astCtxt->equal(this->astCtxt->extract(6, 6, op1), this->astCtxt->bvtrue()), this->astCtxt->bv(6, bvSize1),
15948 this->astCtxt->ite(this->astCtxt->equal(this->astCtxt->extract(7, 7, op1), this->astCtxt->bvtrue()), this->astCtxt->bv(7, bvSize1),
15949 this->astCtxt->bv(0, bvSize1)
15950 ))))))))
15951 );
15952 break;
15953 case triton::size::word:
15954 node = this->astCtxt->ite(
15955 this->astCtxt->equal(op1, this->astCtxt->bv(0, bvSize2)),
15956 this->astCtxt->bv(bvSize1, bvSize1),
15957 this->astCtxt->ite(this->astCtxt->equal(this->astCtxt->extract(0, 0, op1), this->astCtxt->bvtrue()), this->astCtxt->bv(0, bvSize1),
15958 this->astCtxt->ite(this->astCtxt->equal(this->astCtxt->extract(1, 1, op1), this->astCtxt->bvtrue()), this->astCtxt->bv(1, bvSize1),
15959 this->astCtxt->ite(this->astCtxt->equal(this->astCtxt->extract(2, 2, op1), this->astCtxt->bvtrue()), this->astCtxt->bv(2, bvSize1),

16075 this->astCtxt->ite(this->astCtxt->equal(this->astCtxt->extract(54, 54, op1), this->astCtxt->bvtrue()), this->astCtxt->bv(54, bvSize1),
16076 this->astCtxt->ite(this->astCtxt->equal(this->astCtxt->extract(55, 55, op1), this->astCtxt->bvtrue()), this->astCtxt->bv(55, bvSize1),
16077 this->astCtxt->ite(this->astCtxt->equal(this->astCtxt->extract(56, 56, op1), this->astCtxt->bvtrue()), this->astCtxt->bv(56, bvSize1),
16078 this->astCtxt->ite(this->astCtxt->equal(this->astCtxt->extract(57, 57, op1), this->astCtxt->bvtrue()), this->astCtxt->bv(57, bvSize1),
16079 this->astCtxt->ite(this->astCtxt->equal(this->astCtxt->extract(58, 58, op1), this->astCtxt->bvtrue()), this->astCtxt->bv(58, bvSize1),
16080 this->astCtxt->ite(this->astCtxt->equal(this->astCtxt->extract(59, 59, op1), this->astCtxt->bvtrue()), this->astCtxt->bv(59, bvSize1),
16081 this->astCtxt->ite(this->astCtxt->equal(this->astCtxt->extract(60, 60, op1), this->astCtxt->bvtrue()), this->astCtxt->bv(60, bvSize1),
16082 this->astCtxt->ite(this->astCtxt->equal(this->astCtxt->extract(61, 61, op1), this->astCtxt->bvtrue()), this->astCtxt->bv(61, bvSize1),
16083 this->astCtxt->ite(this->astCtxt->equal(this->astCtxt->extract(62, 62, op1), this->astCtxt->bvtrue()), this->astCtxt->bv(62, bvSize1),
16084 this->astCtxt->ite(this->astCtxt->equal(this->astCtxt->extract(63, 63, op1), this->astCtxt->bvtrue()), this->astCtxt->bv(63, bvSize1),
16085 this->astCtxt->bv(0, bvSize1)
16086 ))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))))
16087 );
16088 break;
16089 default:
16090 throw triton::exceptions::Semantics("x86Semantics::tzcnt_s(): Invalid operand size.");
16091 }
16092
16093 /* Create symbolic expression */
16094 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, dst, "TZCNT operation");
16095
16096 /* Spread taint */
16097 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintAssignment(dst, src);
16098
16099 /* Update symbolic flags */
16100 this->cfTzcnt_s(inst, expr, src, op1);
16101 this->zf_s(inst, expr, src);
16102
16103 /* Tag undefined flags */
16104 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_OF));
16105 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_SF));
16106 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_PF));
16107 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_AF));
16108
16109 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
16110 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
16111 }

16347
16348 void x86Semantics::vmovsd_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
16349 /* Move scalar double-precision floating-point value */
16350 if (inst.operands.size() == 2) {
16351 auto& dst = inst.operands[0];
16352 auto& src = inst.operands[1];
16353
16354 /* Create symbolic operands */
16355 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, dst);
16356 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src);
16357
16358 /* Create the semantics */
16359 triton::ast::SharedAbstractNode node;
16360 if (dst.getSize() == triton::size::dqword && src.getSize() == triton::size::qword) {
16361 /* VEX.LIG.F2.0F.WIG 10 /r VMOVSD xmm1, m64 */
16362 node = op2;
16363 }
16364 else if (dst.getSize() == triton::size::qword && src.getSize() == triton::size::dqword) {
16365 /* VEX.LIG.F2.0F.WIG 11 /r VMOVSD m64, xmm1 */
16366 node = this->astCtxt->extract(triton::bitsize::qword - 1, 0, op2);
16367 }
16368 else {
16369 throw triton::exceptions::Semantics("x86Semantics::vmovsd_s(): Invalid operand size.");
16370 }
16371
16372 /* Create symbolic expression */
16373 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, dst, "VMOVSD operation");
16374
16375 /* Spread taint */
16376 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintAssignment(dst, src);
16377 }
16378
16379 /* Merge scalar double-precision floating-point value
16380 *
16381 * VEX.NDS.LIG.F2.0F.WIG 10 /r VMOVSD xmm1, xmm2, xmm3
16382 * VEX.NDS.LIG.F2.0F.WIG 11 /r VMOVSD xmm1, xmm2, xmm3
16383 */
16384 else if (inst.operands.size() == 3) {
16385 auto& dst = inst.operands[0];
16386 auto& src1 = inst.operands[1];
16387 auto& src2 = inst.operands[2];
16388
16389 /* Create symbolic operands */
16390 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, dst);
16391 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src1);
16392 auto op3 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src2);
16393
16394 /* Create the semantics */
16395 auto node = this->astCtxt->concat(
16396 this->astCtxt->extract(triton::bitsize::dqword - 1, triton::bitsize::qword, op2),
16397 this->astCtxt->extract(triton::bitsize::qword - 1, 0, op3)
16398 );
16399
16400 /* Create symbolic expression */
16401 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, dst, "VMOVSD operation");
16402
16403 /* Spread taint */
16404 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintAssignment(dst, src1) | this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src2);
16405 }
16406
16407 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
16408 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
16409 }

16448 void x86Semantics::vpackuswb_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
16449 auto& dst = inst.operands[0];
16450 auto& src1 = inst.operands[1];
16451 auto& src2 = inst.operands[2];
16452
16453 /* Create symbolic operands */
16454 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src1);
16455 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src2);
16456
16457 /* Create the semantics */
16458 std::vector<triton::ast::SharedAbstractNode> pck;
16459 pck.reserve(dst.getSize());
16460
16461 std::vector<triton::ast::SharedAbstractNode> ops{op2, op1};
16462 for (triton::uint32 k = 0; k < dst.getSize() / triton::size::dqword; ++k) {
16463 for (triton::uint32 idx = 0; idx < ops.size(); ++idx) {
16464 for (triton::uint32 i = triton::size::qword * k; i < triton::size::qword * (k + 1); ++i) {
16465 uint32 high = (dst.getBitSize() - 1) - (i * triton::bitsize::word);
16466 uint32 low = (dst.getBitSize() - triton::bitsize::word) - (i * triton::bitsize::word);
16467 auto signed_word = this->astCtxt->extract(high, low, ops[idx]);
16468 pck.push_back(this->astCtxt->ite(
16469 this->astCtxt->bvsge(signed_word, this->astCtxt->bv(0xff, triton::bitsize::word)),
16470 this->astCtxt->bv(0xff, triton::bitsize::byte),
16471 this->astCtxt->ite(
16472 this->astCtxt->bvsle(signed_word, this->astCtxt->bv(0x00, triton::bitsize::word)),
16473 this->astCtxt->bv(0x00, triton::bitsize::byte),
16474 this->astCtxt->extract(triton::bitsize::byte - 1, 0, signed_word)))
16475 );
16476 }
16477 }
16478 }
16479
16480 auto node = this->astCtxt->concat(pck);
16481
16482 /* Create symbolic expression */
16483 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, dst, "VPACKUSWB operation");
16484
16485 /* Apply the taint */
16486 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintAssignment(dst, src1) | this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src2);
16487
16488 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
16489 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
16490 }

16583 void x86Semantics::vpaddb_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
16584 auto& dst = inst.operands[0];
16585 auto& src1 = inst.operands[1];
16586 auto& src2 = inst.operands[2];
16587
16588 /* Create symbolic operands */
16589 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src1);
16590 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src2);
16591
16592 /* Create the semantics */
16593 std::vector<triton::ast::SharedAbstractNode> pck;
16594 pck.reserve(dst.getSize() / triton::size::byte);
16595
16596 for (triton::uint32 i = 0; i < dst.getSize() / triton::size::byte; ++i) {
16597 uint32 high = (dst.getBitSize() - 1) - (i * triton::bitsize::byte);
16598 uint32 low = (dst.getBitSize() - triton::bitsize::byte) - (i * triton::bitsize::byte);
16599 pck.push_back(this->astCtxt->bvadd(this->astCtxt->extract(high, low, op1), this->astCtxt->extract(high, low, op2)));
16600 }
16601 auto node = this->astCtxt->concat(pck);
16602
16603 /* Create symbolic expression */
16604 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, dst, "VPADDB operation");
16605
16606 /* Spread taint */
16607 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintAssignment(dst, src1) | this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src2);
16608
16609 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
16610 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
16611 }

16721
16722 void x86Semantics::vperm2i128_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
16723 auto& dst = inst.operands[0];
16724 auto& src1 = inst.operands[1];
16725 auto& src2 = inst.operands[2];
16726 auto& src3 = inst.operands[3];
16727
16728 /* Create symbolic operands */
16729 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src1);
16730 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src2);
16731 auto op3 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src3);
16732
16733 /* Create the semantics */
16734 std::deque<triton::arch::OperandWrapper> taint;
16735 auto permute = [&] (triton::uint8 control) {
16736 switch (control) {
16737 case 0:
16738 taint.push_back(src1);
16739 return this->astCtxt->extract(127, 0, op1);
16740 case 1:
16741 taint.push_back(src1);
16742 return this->astCtxt->extract(255, 128, op1);
16743 case 2:
16744 taint.push_back(src2);
16745 return this->astCtxt->extract(127, 0, op2);
16746 case 3:
16747 default:
16748 taint.push_back(src2);
16749 return this->astCtxt->extract(255, 128, op2);
16750 }
16751 };
16752
16753 auto ctrl = static_cast<triton::uint8>(op3->evaluate());
16754 auto high = permute((ctrl >> 4) & 0b00000011);
16755 auto low = permute(ctrl & 0b00000011);
16756
16757 if (ctrl & 0b00001000) {
16758 low = this->astCtxt->bv(0, 128);
16759 taint.pop_back();
16760 }
16761
16762 if (ctrl & 0b10000000) {
16763 high = this->astCtxt->bv(0, 128);
16764 taint.pop_front();
16765 }
16766
16767 auto node = this->astCtxt->concat(high, low);
16768
16769 /* Create symbolic expression */
16770 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, dst, "VPERM2I128 operation");
16771
16772 /* Spread taint */
16773 if (taint.empty()) {
16774 this->taintEngine->setTaint(dst, false);
16775 } else if (taint.size() == 1) {
16776 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintAssignment(dst, taint[0]);
16777 } else {
16778 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintAssignment(dst, taint[0]) | this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, taint[0]);
16779 }
16780
16781 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
16782 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
16783 }
16784
16785
16786 void x86Semantics::vpermq_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
16787 auto& dst = inst.operands[0];
16788 auto& src1 = inst.operands[1];
16789 auto& src2 = inst.operands[2];
16790
16791 /* Create symbolic operands */
16792 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src1);
16793 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src2);
16794
16795 /* Create the semantics */
16796 std::vector<triton::ast::SharedAbstractNode> pck;
16797 pck.reserve(dst.getSize() / triton::size::byte);
16798
16799 for (triton::uint32 i = 0; i < dst.getSize() / triton::size::qword; ++i) {
16800 auto high = triton::bitsize::byte - 1 - 2 * i;
16801 auto shift = this->astCtxt->bvmul(
16802 this->astCtxt->bv(triton::bitsize::qword, src1.getBitSize()),
16803 this->astCtxt->zx(src1.getBitSize() - 2,
16804 this->astCtxt->extract(high, high - 1, op2)));
16805 pck.push_back(this->astCtxt->extract(triton::bitsize::qword - 1, 0, this->astCtxt->bvlshr(op1, shift)));
16806 }
16807
16808 auto node = this->astCtxt->concat(pck);
16809
16810 /* Create symbolic expression */
16811 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, dst, "VPERMQ operation");
16812
16813 /* Spread taint */
16814 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src1);
16815
16816 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
16817 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
16818 }

16904
16905 void x86Semantics::vpextrw_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
16906 triton::uint32 count = 0;
16907 auto& dst = inst.operands[0];
16908 auto& src1 = inst.operands[1];
16909 auto& src2 = inst.operands[2];
16910
16911 /*
16912 * When specifying a word location in an MMX technology register, the
16913 * 2 least-significant bits of the count operand specify the location;
16914 * for an XMM register, the 3 least-significant bits specify the
16915 * location.
16916 */
16917 if (src1.getBitSize() == triton::bitsize::qword) {
16918 count = 0x03;
16919 }
16920 else {
16921 count = 0x07;
16922 }
16923
16924 /* Create symbolic operands */
16925 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, dst);
16926 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src1);
16927 auto op3 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src2);
16928
16929 auto node = this->astCtxt->extract(triton::bitsize::word - 1, 0,
16930 this->astCtxt->bvlshr(
16931 op2,
16932 this->astCtxt->bv(((op3->evaluate() & count) * triton::bitsize::word), op2->getBitvectorSize())
16933 )
16934 );
16935
16936 /* Create symbolic expression */
16937 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, dst, "VPEXTRW operation");
16938
16939 /* Apply the taint */
16940 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintAssignment(dst, src1);
16941
16942 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
16943 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
16944 }

16949 auto &src = inst.operands[1];

16951 /* Create symbolic operands */

16970 void x86Semantics::vpcmpeqb_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
16971 auto& dst = inst.operands[0];
16972 auto& src1 = inst.operands[1];
16973 auto& src2 = inst.operands[2];
16974
16975 /* Create symbolic operands */
16976 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src1);
16977 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src2);
16978
16979 /* Create the semantics */
16980 std::vector<triton::ast::SharedAbstractNode> pck;
16981 pck.reserve(dst.getSize());
16982
16983 for (triton::uint32 index = 0; index < src1.getSize(); index++) {
16984 uint32 high = (src1.getBitSize() - 1) - (index * triton::bitsize::byte);
16985 uint32 low = (src1.getBitSize() - triton::bitsize::byte) - (index * triton::bitsize::byte);
16986 pck.push_back(this->astCtxt->ite(
16987 this->astCtxt->equal(
16988 this->astCtxt->extract(high, low, op1),
16989 this->astCtxt->extract(high, low, op2)),
16990 this->astCtxt->bv(0xff, triton::bitsize::byte),
16991 this->astCtxt->bv(0x00, triton::bitsize::byte))
16992 );
16993 }
16994
16995 auto node = this->astCtxt->concat(pck);
16996
16997 /* Create symbolic expression */
16998 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, dst, "VPCMPEQB operation");
16999
17000 /* Apply the taint */
17001 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintAssignment(dst, src1) | this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src2);
17002
17003 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
17004 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
17005 }

17122 void x86Semantics::vpcmpgtb_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
17123 auto& dst = inst.operands[0];
17124 auto& src1 = inst.operands[1];
17125 auto& src2 = inst.operands[2];
17126

17128 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src1);
17129 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src2);
17130
17131 /* Create the semantics */
17132 std::vector<triton::ast::SharedAbstractNode> pck;
17133 pck.reserve(dst.getSize());
17134
17135 for (triton::uint32 index = 0; index < dst.getSize(); index++) {
17136 uint32 high = (dst.getBitSize() - 1) - (index * triton::bitsize::byte);
17137 uint32 low = (dst.getBitSize() - triton::bitsize::byte) - (index * triton::bitsize::byte);
17138 pck.push_back(this->astCtxt->ite(
17139 this->astCtxt->bvsgt(
17140 this->astCtxt->extract(high, low, op1),
17141 this->astCtxt->extract(high, low, op2)),
17142 this->astCtxt->bv(0xff, triton::bitsize::byte),
17143 this->astCtxt->bv(0x00, triton::bitsize::byte))
17144 );
17145 }
17146
17147 auto node = this->astCtxt->concat(pck);

17236 void x86Semantics::vpmaddwd_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
17237 auto& dst = inst.operands[0];
17238 auto& src1 = inst.operands[1];
17239 auto& src2 = inst.operands[2];
17240
17241 /* Create symbolic operands */
17242 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src1);
17243 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src2);
17244
17245 /* Create the semantics */
17246 std::vector<triton::ast::SharedAbstractNode> pck;
17247 pck.reserve(dst.getSize() / triton::size::dword);
17248
17249 for (triton::uint32 i = 0; i < dst.getSize() / triton::size::word; i += 2) {
17250 uint32 high = (dst.getBitSize() - 1) - (i * triton::bitsize::word);
17251 uint32 low = (dst.getBitSize() - triton::bitsize::word) - (i * triton::bitsize::word);
17252 auto node1 = this->astCtxt->bvmul(
17253 this->astCtxt->sx(triton::bitsize::word, this->astCtxt->extract(high, low, op1)),
17254 this->astCtxt->sx(triton::bitsize::word, this->astCtxt->extract(high, low, op2))
17255 );
17256 high -= triton::bitsize::word;
17257 low -= triton::bitsize::word;
17258 auto node2 = this->astCtxt->bvmul(
17259 this->astCtxt->sx(triton::bitsize::word, this->astCtxt->extract(high, low, op1)),
17260 this->astCtxt->sx(triton::bitsize::word, this->astCtxt->extract(high, low, op2))
17261 );
17262 pck.push_back(this->astCtxt->bvadd(node1, node2));
17263 }
17264
17265 auto node = this->astCtxt->concat(pck);
17266
17267 /* Create symbolic expression */
17268 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, dst, "VPMADDWD operation");
17269
17270 /* Apply the taint */
17271 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintAssignment(dst, src1) | this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src2);
17272
17273 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
17274 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
17275 }

17278 void x86Semantics::vpmovmskb_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {

17284

17292 mskb.push_back(this->astCtxt->extract(247, 247, op2));
17293 mskb.push_back(this->astCtxt->extract(239, 239, op2));

17299 mskb.push_back(this->astCtxt->extract(191, 191, op2));
17300 mskb.push_back(this->astCtxt->extract(183, 183, op2));
17301 mskb.push_back(this->astCtxt->extract(175, 175, op2));
17302 mskb.push_back(this->astCtxt->extract(167, 167, op2));

17312 mskb.push_back(this->astCtxt->extract(103, 103, op2));
17313 mskb.push_back(this->astCtxt->extract(95 , 95 , op2));
17314 mskb.push_back(this->astCtxt->extract(87 , 87 , op2));
17315 mskb.push_back(this->astCtxt->extract(79 , 79 , op2));
17316 mskb.push_back(this->astCtxt->extract(71 , 71 , op2));
17317 mskb.push_back(this->astCtxt->extract(63 , 63 , op2));
