17385 void x86Semantics::vpmulhw_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
17386 auto& dst = inst.operands[0];
17387 auto& src1 = inst.operands[1];
17388 auto& src2 = inst.operands[2];
17389
17390 /* Create symbolic operands */
17391 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src1);
17392 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src2);
17393
17394 /* Create the semantics */
17395 if ((!op1->isSymbolized() && op1->evaluate() == 0) ||
17396 (!op2->isSymbolized() && op2->evaluate() == 0)) {
17397 auto node = this->astCtxt->bv(0, dst.getBitSize());
17398 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, dst, "VPMULHW operation");
17399 this->taintEngine->setTaint(dst, false);
17400 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
17401 return;
17402 }
17403
17404 std::vector<triton::ast::SharedAbstractNode> pck;
17405 pck.reserve(dst.getSize() / triton::size::word);
17406
17407 for (triton::uint32 i = 0; i < dst.getSize() / triton::size::word; ++i) {
17408 uint32 high = (dst.getBitSize() - 1) - (i * triton::bitsize::word);
17409 uint32 low = (dst.getBitSize() - triton::bitsize::word) - (i * triton::bitsize::word);
17410 auto n1 = this->astCtxt->sx(triton::bitsize::word, this->astCtxt->extract(high, low, op1));
17411 auto n2 = this->astCtxt->sx(triton::bitsize::word, this->astCtxt->extract(high, low, op2));
17412 auto node = this->astCtxt->extract(triton::bitsize::dword - 1, triton::bitsize::word, this->astCtxt->bvmul(n1, n2));
17413 pck.push_back(node);
17414 }
17415 auto node = this->astCtxt->concat(pck);
17416
17417 /* Create symbolic expression */
17418 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, dst, "VPMULHW operation");
17419
17420 /* Apply the taint */
17421 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintAssignment(dst, src1) | this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src2);
17422
17423 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
17424 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
17425 }

17494 void x86Semantics::vpshufd_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
17495 auto& dst = inst.operands[0];
17496 auto& src = inst.operands[1];
17497 auto& ord = inst.operands[2];
17498 triton::uint32 dstSize = dst.getBitSize();
17499
17500 /* Create symbolic operands */
17501 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src);
17502 auto op3 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, ord);
17503
17504 /* Create the semantics */
17505 std::vector<triton::ast::SharedAbstractNode> pack;
17506 pack.reserve(8);
17507
17508 switch (dstSize) {
17509
17510 /* YMM */
17511 case triton::bitsize::qqword:
17512 pack.push_back(
17513 this->astCtxt->extract(31, 0,
17514 this->astCtxt->bvlshr(
17515 op2,
17516 this->astCtxt->bvmul(
17517 this->astCtxt->zx(dstSize-2, this->astCtxt->extract(7, 6, op3)),
17518 this->astCtxt->bv(32, dstSize)
17519 )
17520 )
17521 )
17522 );
17523 pack.push_back(
17524 this->astCtxt->extract(31, 0,
17525 this->astCtxt->bvlshr(
17526 op2,
17527 this->astCtxt->bvmul(
17528 this->astCtxt->zx(dstSize-2, this->astCtxt->extract(5, 4, op3)),
17529 this->astCtxt->bv(32, dstSize)
17530 )
17531 )
17532 )
17533 );
17534 pack.push_back(
17535 this->astCtxt->extract(31, 0,
17536 this->astCtxt->bvlshr(
17537 op2,
17538 this->astCtxt->bvmul(
17539 this->astCtxt->zx(dstSize-2, this->astCtxt->extract(3, 2, op3)),
17540 this->astCtxt->bv(32, dstSize)
17541 )
17542 )
17543 )
17544 );
17545 pack.push_back(
17546 this->astCtxt->extract(31, 0,
17547 this->astCtxt->bvlshr(
17548 op2,
17549 this->astCtxt->bvmul(
17550 this->astCtxt->zx(dstSize-2, this->astCtxt->extract(1, 0, op3)),
17551 this->astCtxt->bv(32, dstSize)
17552 )
17553 )
17554 )
17555 );
17556
17557 /* XMM */
17558 case triton::bitsize::dqword:
17559 pack.push_back(
17560 this->astCtxt->extract(31, 0,
17561 this->astCtxt->bvlshr(
17562 op2,
17563 this->astCtxt->bvmul(
17564 this->astCtxt->zx(dstSize-2, this->astCtxt->extract(7, 6, op3)),
17565 this->astCtxt->bv(32, dstSize)
17566 )
17567 )
17568 )
17569 );
17570 pack.push_back(
17571 this->astCtxt->extract(31, 0,
17572 this->astCtxt->bvlshr(
17573 op2,
17574 this->astCtxt->bvmul(
17575 this->astCtxt->zx(dstSize-2, this->astCtxt->extract(5, 4, op3)),
17576 this->astCtxt->bv(32, dstSize)
17577 )
17578 )
17579 )
17580 );
17581 pack.push_back(
17582 this->astCtxt->extract(31, 0,
17583 this->astCtxt->bvlshr(
17584 op2,
17585 this->astCtxt->bvmul(
17586 this->astCtxt->zx(dstSize-2, this->astCtxt->extract(3, 2, op3)),
17587 this->astCtxt->bv(32, dstSize)
17588 )
17589 )
17590 )
17591 );
17592 pack.push_back(
17593 this->astCtxt->extract(31, 0,
17594 this->astCtxt->bvlshr(
17595 op2,
17596 this->astCtxt->bvmul(
17597 this->astCtxt->zx(dstSize-2, this->astCtxt->extract(1, 0, op3)),
17598 this->astCtxt->bv(32, dstSize)
17599 )
17600 )
17601 )
17602 );
17603 break;
17604
17605 default:
17606 throw triton::exceptions::Semantics("x86Semantics::vpshufd_s(): Invalid operand size.");
17607 }
17608
17609 auto node = this->astCtxt->concat(pack);
17610
17611 /* Create symbolic expression */
17612 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, dst, "VPSHUFD operation");
17613
17614 /* Spread taint */
17615 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintAssignment(dst, src);
17616
17617 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
17618 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
17619 }

17655 this->taintEngine->setTaint(dst, false);

17657 /* Update the symbolic control flow */

17662 void x86Semantics::vpslldq_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
17663 auto& dst = inst.operands[0];
17664 auto& src1 = inst.operands[1];
17665 auto& src2 = inst.operands[2];
17666
17667 /* Create symbolic operands */
17668 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src1);
17669 auto op2 = this->astCtxt->zx(triton::bitsize::dqword - src2.getBitSize(), this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src2));
17670
17671 /* Create the semantics */
17672 triton::ast::SharedAbstractNode node;
17673
17674 std::vector<triton::ast::SharedAbstractNode> pck;
17675 pck.reserve(dst.getSize() / triton::size::dqword);
17676
17677 for (triton::uint32 index = 0; index < dst.getSize() / triton::size::dqword; index++) {
17678 uint32 high = (dst.getBitSize() - 1) - (index * triton::bitsize::dqword);
17679 uint32 low = (dst.getBitSize() - triton::bitsize::dqword) - (index * triton::bitsize::dqword);
17680 pck.push_back(this->astCtxt->bvshl(
17681 this->astCtxt->extract(high, low, op1),
17682 this->astCtxt->bvmul(
17683 this->astCtxt->ite(
17684 this->astCtxt->bvuge(op2, this->astCtxt->bv(triton::bitsize::word, triton::bitsize::dqword)),
17685 this->astCtxt->bv(triton::bitsize::word, triton::bitsize::dqword),
17686 op2
17687 ),
17688 this->astCtxt->bv(triton::bitsize::byte, triton::bitsize::dqword)
17689 )
17690 ));
17691 }
17692
17693 node = pck.size() > 1 ? this->astCtxt->concat(pck) : pck[0];
17694
17695 /* Create symbolic expression */
17696 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, dst, "VPSLLDQ operation");
17697
17698 /* Spread taint */
17699 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintAssignment(dst, src1) | this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src2);
17700
17701 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
17702 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
17703 }

17706 void x86Semantics::vpsllw_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
17707 auto& dst = inst.operands[0];
17708 auto& src1 = inst.operands[1];
17709 auto& src2 = inst.operands[2];
17710
17711 /* Create symbolic operands */
17712 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src1);
17713 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src2);
17714
17715 /* Create the semantics */

17717 pck.reserve(dst.getSize() / triton::size::word);
17718
17719 auto shift = this->astCtxt->ite(
17720 this->astCtxt->bvuge(op2, this->astCtxt->bv(triton::bitsize::word, src2.getBitSize())),
17721 this->astCtxt->bv(triton::bitsize::word, src2.getBitSize()),
17722 op2
17723 );
17724
17725 if (shift->getBitvectorSize() < triton::bitsize::word) {
17726 shift = this->astCtxt->zx(triton::bitsize::word - shift->getBitvectorSize(), shift);
17727 }
17728 else {
17729 shift = this->astCtxt->extract(triton::bitsize::word - 1, 0, shift);
17730 }
17731
17732 for (triton::uint32 i = 0; i < dst.getSize() / triton::size::word; ++i) {
17733 uint32 high = (dst.getBitSize() - 1) - (i * triton::bitsize::word);
17734 uint32 low = (dst.getBitSize() - triton::bitsize::word) - (i * triton::bitsize::word);
17735 pck.push_back(this->astCtxt->bvshl(this->astCtxt->extract(high, low, op1), shift));
17736 }
17737 auto node = this->astCtxt->concat(pck);
17738
17739 /* Create symbolic expression */
17740 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, dst, "VPSLLW operation");
17741
17742 /* Spread taint */
17743 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintAssignment(dst, src1) | this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src2);
17744
17745 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
17746 this->controlFlow_s(inst);

18066
18067 void x86Semantics::vptest_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
18068 auto& src1 = inst.operands[0];
18069 auto& src2 = inst.operands[1];
18070
18071 /* Create symbolic operands */
18072 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src1);
18073 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src2);
18074
18075 /* Create the semantics */
18076 auto node1 = this->astCtxt->bvand(op1, op2);
18077 auto node2 = this->astCtxt->bvand(op1, this->astCtxt->bvnot(op2));
18078
18079 /* Create symbolic expression */
18080 auto expr1 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicVolatileExpression(inst, node1, "VPTEST operation");
18081 auto expr2 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicVolatileExpression(inst, node2, "VPTEST operation");
18082
18083 /* Spread taint */
18084 expr1->isTainted = this->taintEngine->isTainted(src1) | this->taintEngine->isTainted(src2);
18085 expr2->isTainted = this->taintEngine->isTainted(src1) | this->taintEngine->isTainted(src2);
18086
18087 /* Update symbolic flags */
18088 this->clearFlag_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_AF), "Clears adjust flag");
18089 this->cfPtest_s(inst, expr2, src1, true);
18090 this->clearFlag_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_OF), "Clears overflow flag");
18091 this->clearFlag_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_PF), "Clears parity flag");
18092 this->clearFlag_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_SF), "Clears sign flag");
18093 this->zf_s(inst, expr1, src1, true);
18094
18095 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
18096 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
18097 }

18099
18100 void x86Semantics::vpunpckhbw_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
18101 auto& dst = inst.operands[0];
18102 auto& src1 = inst.operands[1];
18103 auto& src2 = inst.operands[2];
18104
18105 /* Create symbolic operands */
18106 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src1);
18107 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src2);
18108
18109 /* Create the semantics */
18110 std::vector<triton::ast::SharedAbstractNode> unpack;
18111 unpack.reserve(dst.getSize());
18112
18113 uint32 start_index = dst.getBitSize();
18114 for (triton::uint32 k = 0; k < dst.getSize() / triton::size::dqword; ++k) {
18115 start_index -= k * triton::bitsize::dqword;
18116 for (triton::uint32 i = 0; i < triton::size::dqword / triton::size::word; ++i) {
18117 uint32 high = (start_index - 1) - (i * triton::bitsize::byte);
18118 uint32 low = (start_index - triton::bitsize::byte) - (i * triton::bitsize::byte);
18119 unpack.push_back(this->astCtxt->extract(high, low, op2));
18120 unpack.push_back(this->astCtxt->extract(high, low, op1));
18121 }
18122 }
18123
18124 auto node = this->astCtxt->concat(unpack);
18125
18126 /* Create symbolic expression */
18127 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, dst, "VPUNPCKHBW operation");
18128
18129 /* Apply the taint */
18130 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintAssignment(dst, src1) | this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src2);
18131
18132 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
18133 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
18134 }

18188 for (triton::uint32 k = 0; k < dst.getSize() / triton::size::dqword; ++k) {
18189 start_index -= k * triton::bitsize::dqword;
18190 for (triton::uint32 i = 0; i < triton::size::dqword / triton::size::dqword; ++i) {
18191 uint32 high = (start_index - 1) - (i * triton::bitsize::qword);
18192 uint32 low = (start_index - triton::bitsize::qword) - (i * triton::bitsize::qword);
18193 unpack.push_back(this->astCtxt->extract(high, low, op2));
18194 unpack.push_back(this->astCtxt->extract(high, low, op1));
18195 }
18196 }
18197
18198 auto node = this->astCtxt->concat(unpack);
18199
18200 /* Create symbolic expression */
18201 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, dst, "VPUNPCKHQDQ operation");
18202
18203 /* Apply the taint */
18204 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintAssignment(dst, src1) | this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src2);
18205
18206 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
18207 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
18208 }

18453
18454 void x86Semantics::xadd_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
18455 auto& dst = inst.operands[0];
18456 auto& src = inst.operands[1];
18457 bool dstT = this->taintEngine->isTainted(dst);
18458
18459 /* Create symbolic operands */
18460 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, dst);
18461 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src);
18462
18463 /* Create the semantics */
18464 auto node = this->astCtxt->bvadd(op1, op2);
18465
18466 /* Create symbolic expression */
18467 auto expr1 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, op1, src, "XADD operation");
18468 auto expr2 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, dst, "XADD operation");
18469
18470 /* Spread taint */
18471 expr2->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src);
18472 expr1->isTainted = this->taintEngine->setTaint(src, dstT);
18473
18474 /* Update symbolic flags */
18475 this->af_s(inst, expr2, dst, op1, op2);
18476 this->cfAdd_s(inst, expr2, dst, op1, op2);
18477 this->ofAdd_s(inst, expr2, dst, op1, op2);
18478 this->pf_s(inst, expr2, dst);
18479 this->sf_s(inst, expr2, dst);
18480 this->zf_s(inst, expr2, dst);
18481
18482 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
18483 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
18484 }

18486
18487 void x86Semantics::xchg_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
18488 auto& dst = inst.operands[0];
18489 auto& src = inst.operands[1];
18490 bool dstT = this->taintEngine->isTainted(dst);
18491 bool srcT = this->taintEngine->isTainted(src);
18492
18493 /* Create symbolic operands */
18494 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, dst);
18495 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src);
18496
18497 /* Create the semantics */
18498 auto node1 = op2;
18499 auto node2 = op1;
18500
18501 /* Create symbolic expression */
18502 auto expr1 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node1, dst, "XCHG operation");
18503 auto expr2 = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node2, src, "XCHG operation");
18504
18505 /* Spread taint */
18506 expr1->isTainted = this->taintEngine->setTaint(dst, srcT);
18507 expr2->isTainted = this->taintEngine->setTaint(src, dstT);
18508
18509 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
18510 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
18511 }

18513
18514 void x86Semantics::xor_s(triton::arch::Instruction& inst) {
18515 auto& dst = inst.operands[0];
18516 auto& src = inst.operands[1];
18517
18518 /* Create symbolic operands */
18519 auto op1 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, dst);
18520 auto op2 = this->symbolicEngine->getOperandAst(inst, src);
18521
18522 /* Create the semantics */
18523 auto node = this->astCtxt->bvxor(op1, op2);
18524
18525 /* Create symbolic expression */
18526 auto expr = this->symbolicEngine->createSymbolicExpression(inst, node, dst, "XOR operation");
18527
18528 /* Spread taint */
18529 /* clear taint if the registers are the same */
18530 if (dst.getType() == OP_REG && src.getRegister() == dst.getRegister())
18531 this->taintEngine->setTaint(src, false);
18532 else
18533 expr->isTainted = this->taintEngine->taintUnion(dst, src);
18534
18535 /* Update symbolic flags */
18536 this->undefined_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_AF));
18537 this->clearFlag_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_CF), "Clears carry flag");
18538 this->clearFlag_s(inst, this->architecture->getRegister(ID_REG_X86_OF), "Clears overflow flag");
18539 this->pf_s(inst, expr, dst);
18540 this->sf_s(inst, expr, dst);
18541 this->zf_s(inst, expr, dst);
18542
18543 /* Update the symbolic control flow */
18544 this->controlFlow_s(inst);
18545 }
